title: Good and Evil
author: valerie
text: to sing a song of the day,  to sing a song of the night,  to sing a song is to sing a song with jubilee and delight.   to come forthwith and yonder,  unto the arising sun,  brings to me to ponder,  of that of which is done.   be silent,  my wondering mind,  of that now,  which has been,  to call upon the feather-winged,  and restore me back from sin.   i am only here to observe,  to learn from mistakes before,  but sometimes,  my dear friend,  there are things you canâ’t ignore.   take me away from the dark,  bring me to the  light,  for i have fallen,  and lost my way,  and i canâ’t get back from the night.   thank you,  oh marvelous one,  to you,  i am indebted,   for taking away my woes,  and my condemnment intercepted.   in you,  i find forgiveness,  though i am earthly still,  but i know that when the time comes,  i am in your will.

title: I Hope School Ends
author: vanisha
text: itâ’s my first day at my new school,  i have no friends,  i have nothing to do.  the doddery desks are all in straight rows,  i hate the blue and white uniforms,  why canâ’t i just wear my normal clothes? iâ’m on a meandering roller coaster that never ends,  going through ups and downs and mysterious bends.  my terrifying teacher pronounces my name wrong,  all the ghastly kids laugh all day long.  at lunchtime i sit all alone,  playing and texting on my ruined mobile phone.  next day is even worse,  itâ’s like some nasty witch has sent me a curse.  the guy opposite me gets me in trouble,  i talked back to the teacher,  my detention became double.  i watch the other kids play all day,  with smiling faces on display.  how come their frowns are upside down? i think mine,  just doesnâ’t want to whirl around.  i wish i could go back to how things were,  i miss my old friends; now only a distant blur.

title: An Endless Love
author: vanisha
text: thereâ’s something special in your eyes,  your breath is the wind that makes my heart fly like a kite.  how do i pass the days and nights without you? thoughts float throughout my head,  what do i do?  without you,  i could not live,  i die,   i wait impatiently to drown in your eyes.  when youâ’ve gone the world seems an empty place,   iâ’m running in an endless race.   when a dream shatters in a flash,  i know youâ’ll always be there in a dash.  the light radiating from you is a spectacular view,  makes even the moonlight a pale shadow compared to you.    my love for you no words can tell,  but soon weâ’ll have to say farewell.

title: Oh, My Dear
author: victoria
text: open your eyes and take a look around you.  everything used to be so dull and blue.  that was before you came.  when you started to walk towards me,  you washed it all away.  your smile brightened even my darkest days.  you're like a little tree or perhaps a blooming bud.  growing,  and showing everyone your care and love to the world.  to friends and foes.   you were like a child tucked underneath my wing.  but i had to set you free.  so you could fix all the broken souls.  and show them your heart of gold.  you were never harsh and cold.  not even to ones who deserved it.  oh my dear,  you're just perfect in every way.

title: Bath at the Beach!
author: vinitra
text: the water laps my feet,  as i stretch lazily,  basking in the last rays of the setting sun,  yet enjoying the cool water upon my feet.   i lay down upon the golden sand,  to watch the sun sink below the horizon.   i get up with a sigh,  dusting the grains of sand off me,  i look at the turquoise water,  as though bidding farewell.   i walk to the shower-room for a quick wash,  and wrapping a towel around me,  walk back home.

title: September

title: Life is a Fertile Field
author: vinitra
text: life is a fertile field,  you can choose what you want to grow,  careful while you plant your seed,  remember,  you reap what you sow.   nurture the plants with love and care,  for theyâ’re the experiences of your life,  always mind how you fare,  learn from the happiness and the strife.

title: A Thunderstorm
author: vinitra
text: the rain rages in a fit of fury,  whirling and whistling and moaning,  maybe i will be able to see,  at least ten feet ahead in the morning.   as my car moves slowly along the road,  carefully,  slipping and sliding,  i wish that i could close my eyes.  instead i yawn my sleep away.   i struggle to keep myself awake,  to concentrate on the road,  but i find it very difficult,  iâ’m lonely,  lonely and bored.   i see a pair of headlights behind me,  and sit up straight with joy,  but the other car passes by at furious speed,  iâ’m lonely,  lonely and bored.

title: A Gentle Bride
author: vinitra
text: decked with jewelry and bridal gold,  mixed fear and happiness her eyes hold,   her anklets made a silent sound,  letting her beauty seem profound,   she lifted her head gently only to see,  her silent admirer,  her husband-to-be,   her hair was tied back neatly enough,  her feature made better with a powder puff,   she came down the stairs with shyness untold,  her beauty extravagant,  a character of gold,   a swish of her skirt,  made heads turn,  a slender body,  delicate as a fern.   none could appear happier or fancier,  carrying within a grave secret â– cancer!

title: My Grandpa
author: vithusha
text: the way you approached me with your warm and welcoming grin and your affectionate blessings is still my memory long treasured from the moments you gave me pride â‘till the time you helped me up every time i fell to the ground,  is still carved in my heart iâ’m just an ordinary person that was waiting for those astonishing opportunities and experiences; however,  i am blessed to have had those experiences with you  your soothing scent captures me as sleep falls upon my sparkling eyes,  tired with a long summer day with ecstasy and enchantment you rock me in your wooden rocking chair,  tapping me every second,  or so grandfather,  let me tell you one thing… my life is now filled pleasure and bliss because of your delightful chuckles and the affection that you passed on to your future generations although iâ’ve seen you for only a year,  your presence is still engraved in my mind experiencing your joy for a year that is worth 100 years,  meant a lot to me!  a year had passed by with miserably,  no more to come; life is life and you got to live with it all my fears of falling,  failure,  or not getting what i wanted,  washes out of my mind as i fell into the face of the death of my grandfather.  when i see your photograph,  my eyes bursts into tears and my heart pounds firmly on my chest our glances met like crossed swords,  the minute i last saw him â“am i going insane?â” i ask myself as i know there is no turning back â“how could you destroy me and lie right to my face when you said we will be together forever?â” my bed so cold,  my house so silent,  no whisper wouldâ’ve been heard.  did the world stop turning or is this just in my imagination? my spirit beat itself and my blood boiled; not a sensation to be passionate about! i was infinitely happy when you were there grandpa,  you will always be imprinted in my mind and soul even though up in heaven!

title: Humanity, Please read this...Plea

text: human kind the world is roaming,   the world is running,   the world is idle.   peace comes from the roaming of idle nurture,  death comes from the running if roaming hate,   it all ends with one simple sway of tongue,  that is,  greetings oh brother! salam-hu-alaikum,  shalom alaikum,  good day,  bonjour,  ni-hao,  gutentag,  greetings in all languages carry the start of a political and social promise,   to unite as humans,  to unite as human kind,  to remove barriers of evil,  to unite the love of the people.   remember,  we are all one,  hate is spawned from the idleness of sympathy.  people may never see this,  if they do,  please remember to keep this akin to your hearts for you shall never gain success,  if you never recognise love.  let the people see,  what they are missing then one day humans will become humankind.   spread the love,  spread this poem,  even if it is a few dedicated poet-lovers,  who see the cry in this poem,  i myself am new to poetry,  but was born with a love for it,  now it emerges,  in the form of a plea.  plea.  please.     by a human brother,  by somebody,  by somebody who you should care about,  a human in need of love.  we all need love,  no matter how distance this melancholy cry is,  it should not be avoided. . . .   waqar r

title: Selfish

text: i sit here quietly in your embrase,   your soft lips agenst my cold skin,   your hand on mine.   i look into your eyes,  seeking              peace  onlt those eyes hold meaning for me.   but i wont be selfish.   i wish you could stay,  but you say   you need it.   you've become distant,  and you know  it.  will you ever be the same?  your warm hands agenst my neck,    kissing me gently.   i gaze into those eyes,  but all  i see is anger,  and adiction.   you've been hurt before.  i don't   want you to go.   you'll never come back to me.   i don't want to be selfish.  so   you'll never know my true feelings.     i can't take it anymore.  you've   been gone so long,  your image is   fading.    please,  i wanted you to stay with me   forever.  i longed to be with you,  more  deeply than the ocean,  bluer than the sky,  truer than roses.     i wish that i would've told this before   you left.    i prayed that i could keep you,  but you're gone.    you can't see my tears,  while i look at    what's left.    only a cold,  grey stone.    you never heard me,  you wouldn't quit.  if        you would've,  you would here me say,      ''i love you. ''       by: w. c.

title: Reasons
author: willie
text: reasons  i have always done things with a reason.   like with basketball.    the reason i play basketball is to impress my parents or friends.    in my whole life i have always had a reason to do something.   it was either good or bad and all of the things i did was to impress somebody.   i think that is how a lot of people make decisions.    i  would get the most expensive shoes and close,   i would play sports like basketball and track.   i would try to get aâ’s on everything, ( that's everybody though) and  all to impress people.    but then i realized. . . i should not have to try to impress people.   i do not need to give into peer pressure.   i do not have to change who i am!  i do not have to be a different person for the simple reason,  to impress people.    most of the mistakes in my life came from wanting to impress somebody  i should buy shoes because i want to buy shoes,  not thinking about if somebody is going to like them.   i should only play sports because they're fun not to get the approval of my parents.   in my life the reason i  should do everything for myself ,  not to impress somebody,    and     the reason i should do things,  is for the glory of god!

title: Fruit Final Draft
author: zach
text: every person is some type of fruit,  and some are even multiple fruits.  all people are berries,  which come in different shapes and sizes.   some people are bitter lemons.   but some people are the sweet grapes.   some are large melons with their large personality others are the shy blackberry with their low key tone.  while some people are very sophisticated pineapples,  hard to open other people are the plain and simple apple,  with no barrier.   while some people are low maintenance pears,  who never think about themselves the rest are high maintenance cherry trees who care about nobody except themselves.   some people are apple cores,  hiding their secrets for none to see.   but most people are strawberries,  holding their secrets out in the open for all to see.   unfortunately every fruit is subject to illness and death and the same goes for all people be the right fruit,  because you may one day regret being the sour lemon.

title: To You

text: if i was  the only girl in the world  and you were the only guy in the world.  would you still hate me? or would you forgive me? if only we,  if only.  would you forgive all my mistakes? or would you hate me forever for sakes? because their is love in my heart and i really mean it.  and theirs a painful feeling inside me,  that tells me that you belong besides me.  so what i am trying to say is that i'm really sorry.  and i hope you can forgive me for all my mistakes.  those i did so that your heart thay would not take.  but now i found out that that was the biggest mistake.  because i know you don't like me,  especially not love me.  but we can always start by being friends.  only if thats okay with you.

title: Life is that way

text: it was a hot noon i was cycling down the street the walkman in my ear,  the sweat band around my wrist the hot loo blowing and the sun scorching.    the heat tearing my body and the sweat trickling down my fore head the sight of the kids bathing (in the sea) like a daily chore and  the sight increase my anxiousness to reach the shore  more and more.   and when i reached the shore,  the cool breeze blowing past me and i got the sensation on the shore as if all the troubles had tore and that was the dead end of them.   and when i dived in the sea  and the chill running down my spine the kids splashing the water  and the sea treating them as its own daughter.   this action of mine had reminded of thee of the life of man that after reaching the infinity there is eternity.

title: Struggling
author: abby
text: they say there's something to live for but can you live in half? in two? no.  not with a heart that's torn.   shattering.  crumbling.   life is nothing without him.  i can't stop my love.  i don't think i want to.   breaking.  shredding.   i can't remember when i was happy.  was there ever a time? no.  i can't remember now.   falling.  fading.   you're more monster than human more haze than face.  the pain is the only sure thing now.   slipping.  sliding.   my life is winter the same as in your heart of ice your heart of stone.   burning.  writhing.   and wouldn't that be a blessing?  to have a hardened heart to be alone.   fearing.  hiding.   wouldnâ’t it be a blessing to be alone? to have never met? to be whole?  searing.  screaming.   i havenâ’t touched the knife in a while but iâ’m on itâ’s edge.  iâ’m alone.  so alone.   breaking.  cutting.     relief.  release.   the blood.  the tears.  the salt.  are you happy? are you grinning your endearing,  demonâ’s smile?  memories.  fleeing.   the knife hits the floor as i run out the door.  the sun.  the wind.  itâ’s real.  too real.   life.  death.   life is death without you.  but i can still bleed.  why am i here?  chatter.  noise.   they canâ’t hear me no teachers,  no friends no emotion  the door.  the darkness.   iâ’m back to the darkness.  blood on the floor.  the need to bleach is back to wipe the stain away.   white.  new.   why canâ’t someone help me? why canâ’t he wash you away? wash me away?  pain.  sorrow.   oh god,  please.  iâ’m on my knees.  humbled by your strength.  and humbled by his.   hope.  light.   you are my last resort my only hope.  this is a truly twisted world.   shedding.  remembering.   god,  take him away.  i need you.  i donâ’t need him.   emptiness.  healing.   wipe me clean,  lord.   wash him away.  let me start new.   fresh.  clean.   and the demon was gone.  banished.  a new light for my life.

title: Grandad- a poem for my hero
author: abigale
text: im staring at you photo trying to be brave thinking of  the good times as i picture your face  nothing had prepared me for how i feel today if life is so amazing  why did it take you away  i miss our conversations things no one else could see i miss having a hero the one i want to be  i miss the way you warmed our hands when winter was unfair i miss the smell of cleanliness the softness of your hair  i pulled out your jacket from the wadrobe it came i held it as if were you and your smell came back again  it lingered round a while then it slowly disappeared it felt like you were leaving rolled down my cheek a tear  i always watch your space where you sat on your chair reading your newspaper i look but your not there  i wonder in the kitchen with my hand i trace your seat wishing you were here so i could sit and watch you eat  i miss your random singing your random dancing too i miss how you would joke about and wind grandma up too  there never was a dull moment  while i was in your care i feel ive lost myself without you im bare  emotion is a word although they serve you well i feel i cant express them like ive gone back in my shell  what id give to have a hug from you a kiss,  a smile would do  if i could tell you one thing  it would be that i love you

text: whent life gets cold,  and love is lost,  theirs no where to turn,  without seeing blocks,  when the skies have fallen,  and hevens have dawned,  theirs no where to turn,  without feeling torn.   so many people thought you'd fail,  that you'd end up in a prison jail,  but no one could see what lies beneth,  the beauty you share and all that is peace.   the way you laughed and joked around,  to hide what was really going down,  the thoughts of pain and death they said,  would haunt you with the tears you shed,  no one can save you from the devils hands,  no one likes you,  go home,  your going down,  but now your gone,  they want you back,  no one to hurt,  to watch fight back,  the suffering they put you through,  to watch,  and laugh,  and torchur you.   the teachers wont listen,  your family too,  an all you can think is,  their in this too.   they punchh,  and kick,  and spit on your shoes,  they call you names,  till you lose your cool,  and yes! sticks and stones will break my bones,  but you'll never no what names can do,  they can kill you on the outside,  they can kill you on the in,  even if you try not,  to let them think they'll win,  they always try to beat you,  make you feel dim,  so who are these trajic people,  that hurt you from within,  they say their your friends,  and their there till the ends.   no one can see what your going through,  they think it's just fun,  what their putting you through,  deep down they no,  what they can do,  but if they turned,  it could be them lot too!!!!!!

title: Out at sea
author: adalaina
text: i don't want to imagine the day we depart,  but i find myself doing it more often lately.  i'm crazy enough to want to believe that you could stay next to me,  loyal to me,  forever with me.  and i believed that for a little awhile.  until the voices started yelling and telling me over and over that you did it once and why won't it happen again? i silenced it as much as i could,  but we all have a weak point.  the point of worries and the point where you let go of something you held onto so tightly.   i let go of the comfortability or hope for a slight second,  and when my vision wasn't being clouded with i love you's and beautiful images,  i saw everything i've wiped out of my mind for too long.   everything i didn't want to.  one small mistake,  triggers a big reaction.  didn't we learn that the hard way? so you said you cared for her in the same way you did for me.  or in simpler terms,  i have feelings for you.  and my stomach sank and everything i've known became a question.  forever.  always.  only.  you.  forever with who? always what? only me or her? even myself.   one small mistake who were you planning to spend your forever with,  i thought it was me but even you said it was in question.  how could one fight make that forever,  a possibly.  always.  always what? i always want you beside me and i will always love you,  turned into what does that mean to you.  only? only is one. .  maybe i'm the only girl you thought could make you feel this way,  but how many only's could there be in the world and how many of them can your curiosity refrain from discovering. .  me? was i really worth so little.  was i really not this special thing put on a top step. .  for you. .   now i question every single breathe you take towards me and every single word i question if your vocabulary just isn't big enough to use a different one.  i question your answers and your promises and your everything because you questioned what the words you handed to me really meant to you,  once.   big reaction  so yes,  a month ago i was flaming colors and laughs with a sore stomach.  telling secrets and skipping like the entire world was right at my feet and everything i've ever wanted was here next to me.  and today,  i lay in my bed,  and look at the window for so long waiting for an answer to just flow in the breeze of what i should do.  should i stop staring? should i tell you my thoughts and see what you think. .  will you talk my worries down or will you agree.  i don't want either.  i don't want to be here. .  i wanted to be there,  with you and a smile and some nice weather and an ocean full of content.  but that's not where we are.  i'm in the middles of a dark ocean  during a hurricane waiting for the waves the take me under again and reveal another fish with a text that proves you don't love me how you say you do.  so why can't i bring myself to grab the life jacket,  and the rope that will pull me to shore.  because you are the storm and though terrifying,  the moment i got pushed under for so long and came up again,  was a moment of relief,  thankfulness,  and happiness.  the times you aren't hurting me,  your making me happy and at the shore it will be all to calm and i will have to think about being stuck out at sea for months until it subsides.  but when i'm first out,  it'll be all too much.  and somehow i will wish i was still out there,  full of worry and not thinking about it,  just fighting to breathe.  i fight harder against your waves than i can my own thoughts.  that is why i stay out at sea,

title: Firefighting
author: adalberto
text: on a wonderful sunny morning day.  going to work feeling grateful and true.  hearing the alarm,  listen to what they say.  fire burning mad melting metal blue.  rushing to the destination a light,  shining so bright glowing like fire red.  don't give up,  donâ’t back down,  without a fight.  put out those flames save those soon to be dead.  with darkness around there might not be hope.  as time goes by hope searches a for  soul.  tie knots hard,  make them bind into a rope.  realize the danger,  search for a hole.  firefighting,  dangerous,  is my plan.  if you seek the thrill you'll become a fan.

title: Wounded Soilder
author: adria
text: why do you deny yourself,  oh love? shot in the battlefield of love.   the piercing of a steel piece to  the heart.  hand to the wound you look up at the shooter and  gasp.  could it be she? she the moon and sun she who you cried to she who you dreamed  of a thousand stars.   your blood is on my hands  iâ’ve seen a wound like this  before,  as i carry a scar from it.   i know the pain of tore heart strings.  no blood flow to the chambers.  every breath feels like your last.  but still,  you deny your healing,  oh love  to sew you back into one.   i hear your screams and your cries but still i refuse to let you die.

title: The Shark Poem
author: adrian
text: shark poem  a shark is a fish with really big teeth.  theyâ’ll eat you whole head,  hands,  and feet.  when there hungry theyâ’ll track you down.  theyâ’ll sniff you out like a blood- hound.  they lurk in the water,  hungry,  and waiting.  they might even get you when you are bathing.  many species and most are friendly,  but i donâ’t care.  all of those sharks can give me a scare.  i really like the sharks of the deep.  the knowledge of them is to treasure and keep.

title: Wonderments race
author: adrian
text: it looked extremely well for wonderment the dog favored to win the race.  the top two dogs were out that day ill in a flu like state.   people placed there bets on him to win a splendid fashion.  the other racers were not favored not one to win by a hair.   so it went nearing the race the owner of great wonderment standing bold and straight.  the racers entered the starting gate hoping for nothing that day.   the fans had entered the stadium with bets and drinks in hand.  watching great wonderment as he knew no fear at all.   the announcer called each dog off at a time but no one got more attention than wonderment the great.   the starting pistol rang in a blaze of fire as the hounds went for their prey.  people rang with happiness as they neared the end.  it was fury at the finish where the winner was found out,  but it was not great wonderment no,  for he was still in the starting gate sleeping with his tongue hanging out.

title: Is war the solution
author: adrian
text: the pen is no mightier than the sword,  as war has become inevitable.  leaders only seek the greater reward,  played have memories unforgettable.  we know with our conflicts come death and blood,  yet we kill with a lack of self control.  only when the body sounds of a thud,  do we think we have accomplished a goal.  our children missed as soon as they were flown,  quickly they leave just after selection.  parents heartbroken out living their own,  and in the end they miss their affection.  rather watching the ongoing blood bath,  we should be ending the butchers death wrath.

title: Invisible
author: alayna
text: invisible being invisible is like being a ghost being a ghost is like not existing.  the only one who can see you is your shadow your companion who never leaves you but ignores you throughout the day.    somedays you have to burst into colour from the shades of grey but you know that you know that darkness will overcome you again like the power going out during a storm  wrote it down on the walls,  you were screaming it out you made it clear,  you're still here,  are they listening now? youâ’re just a ghost in the halls there vacant now   you burst out being seen again but quickly disappear into the darkness.   waiting and waiting for it to turn back on forever                                                                                    but you know it's going to take a while it would be too easy to say you're  invisible.                                                                                    instead you feel painfully visible and entirely ignored were built to keep you safe                                                                                  but the walls fall down everybodys different and you are too change what you like and what you like                                                                                                 but it doesn't work you're different,  to different                                                                                        so different that it doesn't matter to you                                                                                                   so different that it doesn't matter to the world.  you dont know that it's good to be different                                                                                  outstanding from everyone else                                                                                                      at some point you realize that your on your own                                                                              you were meant to live in your own world                                                                                        changing the world                                                                                                                                   and making everything better for yourself yes you were a ghost but you had nobody to bring you down                                                              and tear you apart you love the ones that saw you when you were invisible to everyone else                                   the ones that helped you get back on your feet                                                                               the ones that brought you into their lives engulfing title: The Sailor Bracelet
author: alexis
text: the sailor bracelet                                                                                                                          one day i found a bracelet walking along a windy beach my friends told me it was called a sailor i look at them in disbelief i said to them â“ this is just a plain bracelet it neednâ’t have a nameâ” but they said,  â“this is special keep it with you and your whole world will changeâ” so i believed them even though i knew what it was i took it home on my wrist and it never left its spot i then realized that i never took it off i washed with it i wore it to school it was now a part of me  i thought it very cool.  one day i thought it was gone but there it was ready for me  and i stared at it  look to see the change i couldnâ’t see the difference  but there was something missing,  something was wrong and then it finally hit me the color was suddenly gone at that day on my lucky beach the bracelet had been blue now it was just plain white like cotton on a line  i think i like it better this way i thought then to let the thought go  and kept on going just as i had before like i hadnâ’t a care in the world  days and days went by,  just like the seasons the bracelet was still there but it felt different i knew what the change was i didnâ’t ever speak it i knew the summer was coming and i thought i would miss place it as the summer went by day by lazy day  i kept it with me always like a precious gift then one day  i went to that same lazy old beach the twisty curvy one the one i had found my precious bracelet in its sand the one i had spent many a summer at  as i walked along the beach one day i was swishing my feet in its sand i felt something hard hit my foot and when i put my hand do to get it  my bracelet was suddenly gone i traveled back the way i had come hopelessly searching for the precious thing i had lost i dug and kicked but i found nothing until i reached down and felt something i recognized it instantly because i had grown so fond of its touch  my most valued treasure lay there amidst in sand i felt a big wave of relieve my hidden treasure had been found as i put it back into its spot i said softly to myself â“ you will never leave my wrist again you little precious oneâ”  that bracelet never left my wrist again and i am happy for that this is the thing that has brought my joy this is the thing that has brought me happiness this thing a pure,  useless bracelet is now my only one my useless bracelet even thought it is very special i have chosen its name its name is sailor.

title: The Moment I Knew
author: amaria
text: i looked your way,   my gaze caught yours.  it was automatic.  brown orbs met dark,  soulful eyes,  time seemed to stand still.  you seemed to know all of my heart,   everything that i had been holding back my body was a live wire,  the world around us becoming silent,  for none of it mattered i took in every feature of your glorious face: your dimples,  your chocolate eyes,  and your smile i replayed all of the moments leading up to now,  making this even more inevitable; all of the late nights,  giggles,  and blushes.  how you could make me feel overwhelmed and euphoric like no one else could.  i couldnâ’t seem to move,  as our moment lasted a little longer,   just you and i existing.  suddenly,  seemingly in fast motion,  it was as if it never happened.   sound began again,  people moving around us.   it couldnâ’t have been more than two seconds,  but it felt like a beautiful lifetime.  my mouth felt like a desert,  and my limbs still were heavy.  no longer looking at me,  you went on your merry way.  i tried to catch my breath.  â“amaria, â” a random person called.  i turned to them,  not recognizing my voice when i answered.  my eyes couldnâ’t focus.  â“weâ’re leaving, â” they said.  the rest of them had left,  and it was just us two.   i was selfishly causing them to have to wait,  but i couldnâ’t truly care.   i nodded slowly,  my head spinning.   i walked out of the noisy room,  reluctant.   my heart still was palpitating,  as i looked back at you.  i glossed over your perfection once more before swallowing.  that was the moment i knew.

title: My Inner Self

text: i see a girl slowly walking along,  she is not surounded by friends,  she's alone and away from everything,  as if she's in another world,  which she can see but can't get in to,  that's  what keeps her going on into the rain,  as it pours on her,  like a shower that has no mercy,  not a light rain but a hard cruel storm,  wishing she had one good friend that knew her,  sure she had ''friends'',  that left her when her car broke down,  even when her credit card was taken away.  she wants to be in the majority again,  but then again no,  she wants to be in a minority so she can have true friends for once.  being surrounded by friends that listen,  that actually care,  instead she is forgotten left aside like yesterdays friend of the week,  no one ever asked her if she wanted a ride,  she quit asking for a long time.  ago,  she always felt so unwanted when she did ask,  so now she walked with pain and memorys surrouning her like the rain,  each drop a memory of pain,  she knew love and forgot it,  she had it in her grasp but lost it,  it was so nice but then mean,  she tried to come back to him,  he rejected her,  she was hit with an arow right in the heart,  her dream world is the only thing that keeps her alive,  where everyone lisens,  where she is loved,  where she has that one true friend,  where there is no rain,  no sadness,  no pain,  no heart ache,  now she remains in this world as she walks home,  its on the horizen,  shes home alone again,  her dad is out to dinner,  she remains in her world,  where she could truly be happy,  as i see this girl it makes me think,  i belive it is my inner self wanting to be exposed,  if it is i am truely alone,

title: The World is Full of Vultures
author: angela
text: the world is full of vultures waiting with a cruel sneer in anticipation  waiting for a new victim pecking away at their prey leaving only minuscule specks of flesh and carcass the vultures feed upon the fragile and timid so that they can feel more self-assured and powerful nobody says anything or tries to stop it in terror of being devoured,  too so,  they just ignore it and shudder as they catch a glimpse of the unfortunate soul that just stands there,  taking the abuse,  believing the malicious things the vultures tell them about themselves and each abrupt,  little,  comment made towards the vulnerable adolescents is yet another agonizing and excruciating bite from their own confidence and self-worth however,  one day,  a brave and valiant lion came his strength and beauty frightened the sufferers and the vultures presumed they had a new collaborator yet,  this stunning lion disregarded the vultures instead,  he went to the aide of the victims the vultures were stunned,  angry,  and determined to make this lion one of their numerous victims their words,  startlingly,  did not have an effect on the lion this infuriated the vultures further the lion continued to help the victims until they were all well again the vultures watched in annoyance as the past victims became stronger and more confident in themselves the vultures knew this was the lions doing so,  the vultures planned an attack they knew it would work since the others were too fearful to fight against them so,  one evening as the lion was sleeping many vultures began to attack the lion struggled but was no match against the innumerable vultures but to the astonishment of the vultures the others came to help the lion the lion had made them stronger and they were extremely thankful the vultures were defeated the world may be full of vultures and there may be only one lion but that one lion can make all the difference.

title: The man with a ram and a lam
author: angus
text: a man with a ram and a lamb  there was a man who had a ram and a lamb in his yard near a heap of sheep.   the man continued to yell and shout  as he was battered to the ground in pain.   he woke up as he was in hospital crying in pain as the nurse was not there to cure it.  he got up and bounded up and down yelling and shouting as loud as loud.   in the car racing home all alone he drove furiously around and around.  he found his way home on the phone to his mum that is dumb.   he found the sheep jumping on his jeep leaping of as he came to bound up and down on him self.  he ran inside like mad like an olympiad  like his granddad did on that very day.   at night he ran to get his ram that was in the dam nearly drowning as he was clowning around.   he ran as fast as a rocket from the dam with his ram and lamb to the house where he found a mouse in the bird house.   he built a gate with his cell mate and decorated it in lightweight decorate.  the sheep were afraid because the gate was custom-made as the men had a trade.

title: Anxiety
author: anna
text: as i sit up in my room, alone upon my bed,  i try to think about the things that run throughout my head.  i feel the light that pours down on me like a spot of grass in the cool,  white snow it feels like everyone's staring at me,  but this feeling,  no one else knows. the room is crowded with people,  yet still i feel i am lost even though it's warm outside, my body is surrounded by frost.  i want to cry,  i want to scream all at the same time,  these feelings that remain in me are sometimes hard to hide.  sympothy i do not want,  that's the last thing on my mind,  but someone who knows what i'm going through,  is what i need to find. i feel like an ant in the corner,  with a magnifier over my head,  it feels as if my brain will explode; it feels as if i were dead.  this feeling,  i fear,  will not go away,  but i pray that someday it will,  and maybe i will find the strength and someday this space will be filled.

title: My Love to Thee
author: anna
text: love is what i feel deep inside of me,  it is what makes me smile when you are near,  you are all my love could ever be,  your words so sweet and kind are all i hear,   you are juliet locked in her tower,  waiting to be let out into the night,  you are my beautiful golden flower,  that rises from her tower to the light,   do you like me like i love you my love? does your heart beat faster when iâ’m around? there is nothing that can compare our love,  together our love is deeply profound,   all the love in my heart is to thee,  and is out for everyone to see.

title: Eyes of a Dove
author: annaliese
text: what is pain that it would give one the full feeling.   it is a full feeling of emptiness in the pit of her very heart.  how does she know when it will cease,  when it will finally depart? what is this hurt that causes so much sorrow in her very being? this girl,  only but a child,  is lost,  not understanding,  not seeing.  she cannot see a life of joy and hope,  only the life that has ripped her dreams apart.  every aspect of her life wears a mask,  and every aspect seems to outsmart.  she has trouble distinguishing true kindness from fake acting. \t it is hard to say when,  if ever,  hope will step in.  if it will say aloud its words she hears only faintly.  everyday she loses part of her true identity.  she drowns in her pain and gets lost in her ever-present sin.   courageous she stands,  earnestly and hopefully she cries out.  to anyone who will dedicate a moment of their day,   to sitting and listening to a life full gray.  feeling assured there is someone who will comfort her drought.  her drought is one of peace,  and her harvest one of doubt.  she remains hopeless and easily led astray.  the thoughts that run through her mind,  are the words she wishes she could unsay.  she mopes around the world,  she walks,  she speaks,  she lives all as she pouts.  her closest friend was her pillow,  the place where she could cry away her pain.   this pain grows just thick enough to cut with a knife.  her hope seems so far away in her rushed,  sinful life.  her world seems full of losses and no positive gains.   but who cares,  or would help this lost soul? who would possibly have a moment to spare? spare some time to a girl whoâ’s life seems threadbare.   to a girl who feels as if she has taken her last toll.  her only wish was that she had some way to control.  if she could control,  she would not make her life so unfair.  if she could control,  she would allow her heart a healthy repair.  the ifâ’s never happen,  so she gives away her dreamy consol.  who,  for this hurting,  young lady,  would possibly lend a helping hand? for this young one in desperate need of encouragement.   this young one so totally weighted by peopleâ’s quick judgment.  hoping she is heard above all the worldly demands.   she longs to find a source of healing,  a source with tangibility.  her life hinders her and gives her a always-present sense of burdens.  this poor girlâ’s heart is cold,  hard,  and completely barren.  but suddenly her soul finds a love that makes all evil things flee.  this girl is at first skeptical seeing how many times her heart has been broken.  she hopes and wishes for this love to be real,  true,  and genuine.  and thankfully,  she finds,  that it is all three.  his love cleaned up her heart which had been harshly blackened.  the love of a god that freely gives peace,  and freely gives hope.  she finally finds one who will not leave her,  for that she is absolutely certain.  her life is still hard and she does still fall,  but this love gives for her fall a cushion.  this god gives her strength that she forcefully uses to cope.   the constant pain that she once felt,  her eyes see in a new way.  she sees them as an opportunity to rise up and far above.  she allows that hurt to be overwhelmed by this new-found love.  this love was the only thing that got her through each day.  her brand new guide gave her every word she needed to say.  it showed her new things,  and gave her eyes of a dove.   she realized all she had been doing wrong,  and she was immediately ashamed of.  but his love and his power abolished her sins and made them burn away.  she strives to follow her father through the constant push and shove.  everything she does,  she does to please her lord.  it helps that she knows that she is significantly adored.  as she recognized this beautiful leader,  she received the eyes of a dove.

title: I Miss  You
author: annette
text: one night i was with my friends,  not thinking one of their lives will soon end.   we were joking and having fun,   everyone was capping on everyone.   it got late and i left home,   then i fell asleep and in the morning i could only hear the phone.   my sister called and said my friend got shot in the head.  my first question was: is he dead?  she told me no and i started to cry,  and all i could say is why oh why  for three whole months our smiles were upside down,   we missed him cause he wasn't around.   on december 18th he passed away,  we were sad cause' we would not see him everday.   his funeral was so sad,  it's true,  but there was nothing we could say or do  i still miss him in my own ways,  but we will meet again someday.

title: The Poem I Wrote For That Lovely Girl
author: anonymous
text: i'm as lovesick as a turtle whose fallen for a dove,  i just can't act the same around the one i love.  every time i see her,  those sparkly green eyes,  those perfect lips,  i just soar into the skies.  but i've left you down below,  and now i can see,  why i'm always so alone,  it's 'cause you're not with me.   i try to talk to you,  i try to explain,  these feeling that i feel,  but it happens again,  my heart explodes,  and i just can't speak,  you're just so beautiful,  you make my mind weak.  and i've had so much fun,  but i know you were bored,  you stood and watched as my lovesick heart soared.   i want to show you my love,  how much i care,  but i'm not good at that,  and it's just not fair,  that you'd rather be elsewhere,  than with me,  because i don't know how to talk,  or how to speak.  and i end up saying nothing,  i just awkwardly stare,  and you stand next to me,  wishing you weren't there.   okay,  that's it!  i've had enough of love's trick,  of love's stupid spell,  it makes me so sick! you stole my heart,  now i look like a fool! i hate love's game,  it's so overbearingly cruel.  i want to be with you,  give you everything,  but love interferes and i end up with nothing.  why must i love someone so beautiful? it makes it so much harder,  for the heart you stole.

title: Where im From
author: anthony
text: where i am from i am from the cover of endless summer and a guy with slicked back hair in a â“silk saint laurent shirtâ” telling me â“these things happenâ” â“when itâ’s dark outâ”  from my first video game; a gameboy with pokã©mon fire red i am from trips to the skate park with mom on a blazing hot summer day and hitting the mats with coach,  feeling for the first time since mom left.  useful after going undefeated and winning every match with a pin i am from coco,  the dog that grew up with until i was twelve i am from parcheesi games like clue,  monopoly,  and cranium with my family on the weekends i am from the apple tree i tried growing with mom whose apples could just never seem to grow right and were so sour i am from mom,  and the guy i am supposed to call dad,  but iâ’ve never really met i am from the days at grade school,  listening to the other kids talk to their parents and wondering,  â“why canâ’t i tell daddy about my day?â” or â“why canâ’t i tell mommy what new things i learned today?â” i am from realizing that i canâ’t tell â“daddyâ” because daddy disappeared,  and i can only tell â“mommyâ” through the phone  i am from those phone calls with mom,  telling corny jokes that were just so funny for hours i am from happiness and adhd i am from working hard and never giving up i am from â“donâ’t forget to count your blessingsâ”… i never did forget to i am from mom; and the wires,  like chains,  that bound her to those machines keeping her with us until they told us to let her go i am from screaming â“wake up!â”  i am from a long heart piercing beep and begging for my mom back i am from not wanting to sleep because every time iâ’d close my eyes iâ’d hear the sound of her voice telling me itâ’s ok i am from one of my first friends from wrestling,  ethan,  and his brother,  mason i am from learning about ethan… and his brother mason the kid i didnâ’t know directly,  but showed me just how short life can be i am from learning that the teenage mutant ninja turtles canâ’t fight everything; not cancer or a coma i am from those moments that make me realize that being happy and being with friends is the most important thing in life and is the best for healing thatâ’s what makes me love life and thatâ’s why i am who i am

title: Live like there is no tomorrow!
author: anushri
text: breathe like it's your last breath of life,  cry like it's your last tear on earth.  love like you've never been hurt,   sing like nobody's listening,  live like it's heaven on earth,  work like you don't need money,  and dance like no one's watching  smile and tears are part of life there are happy days,  and days of strife.  life is a mixture of everything,  like different music on a single string.   throw away your grief  make the most of that day  so that you won't have to say  i wish i would've done better,  because you'll have done your best  we say bad things to the ones we love,  or even go to bed mad,  at the ones we adore.  life is not everlasting,  we don't know when our time is near.   live like this day is your last,  smile like you never knew any sorrow,  forget your fears,  laugh with you heart,  live like there is no tomorrow!

title: The weaver
author: arpan
text: my life is but a weaving,  between my lord and me.  i can't choose the colours nor the pattern i see.   sometimes,  he chooses sorrow and i,  in the foolish pride; forget he sees the upper and i see the under side.   not till the loom is silent,  and the shuttles cease to fly; will, he reveal the pattern,  or tell the reason why.   the dark threads are as needy; in the weaver's skillful hand,  as the threads of gold and silver; in the pattern he has planned.

title: When death was dancing before me
author: arpan
text: when death was dancing before me,  i laid my hands for it.  when life was singing a melancholy song,  i played my part for it.  death said, i was just a fool,  with all my timid deeds.  i used my life as a tool,  for all my filthy needs.  it was my time to go,  cause god had given a calling.  i had no friend or foe,  and my life was falling.  what i needed was just a light,  a light that could help me.  my wish was not to see fright,  but to live longer happily.  my life remained as a woeful pride,  because it never was true.  sadness came with a strong tide,  and washed everything i had to persue. .

title: Inspire Dance
author: asheley
text: â“who inspires me?â” dance is running away,  peace on earth,  solo or duet  these are the words any dancer would describe dance as dance is releasing my emotions,  sweat or tears  leaps and splits eyes squinting too see the mirrors,  while my body engaged in the right position  dance is the shoe i wear in hip-hop,  a way of movement and a way to escape dance is hip hop,  ballet,  modern,  jive,  salsa,  african,  break,  tap,  step,  flamenco,  bollywood,  or jazz who inspires me? the singer,  dancer,  producer,  and songwriter chris brown  his hard work and dedications,  b. e. t awards,  vmas,  and long choreographyâ’s inspires me to dance my best,  but most of all believe in myself dance is the scent of powder the ballerinas use to be able to passã© across the floor dance is the sight of 5 best friends laughing at their silly movement after their rehearsal dance is the sound of the dancers scratching their point shoes across the floor picture frames at the bedside of earlier recitals in the year dance is point shoes in the oven,  burned at the tips with a lighter and sown with a needle dance is a voice announcing the next performer,  while people you never seen shout and cheer in support the support you need to get through the whole dance piece dance is a adventure that never ever ends dance is intensity dance is compassion dance is passion

title: I Can
author: ashley
text: i tell them im not ready but they dont believe me.   how are they gunna throw me back in public schools and leave me.   i can't let these people get a hold of me.  i'm not a fighter anymore,  thats the old me.   new year,  new me,  a new chance to be free.  i'm tired of being locked away doing nothing but worrying about what will happen on the next day.   i'm getting out and i'm not coming back.   i thought being locked up was cool,  but nah it's actually wack.   i promised myself to succeed,  to do good.  i wont let my family down,  because i told them i could.

title: Wind
author: ashley
text: cool and nice against my skin,   flying through my hair blowing it up,  making it a mess.   bringing sounds to my ears and smells to my nose.   like a storm only without the thunder,  lightening,  and rain.   it can be calm or it can be wicked.  causing destruction to the earth or cleaning it of evil.   i never noticed it much,  only when it was noticeable.  making me so cold i shiver,   or cooling me against the intense summer heat.   i never thought much about it,   really though it has always been around me.   it makes me feel powerful when i open my mind to it.   whether its current is strong or weak.  blowing,  blowing,  blowing away everything making me  laugh out in glee,  delight,  joy,  and excitement.   oh how it makes me feel,  i love it!  the powerful,  blowing,  roaring of the mighty,  fierce,  invincible. . .

title: Sam's Inn
author: ashley
text: sam walked through the woods to see a great site.  eventually he came to a house.  peers through windows that ominous night,  he saw a toy car the size of a mouse.  valor and boldness led him to go in.  he went through the entrance and grabbed his prize.  the place he entered was some sort of inn.  twas desolate.  do you know where it lies? exploring this place: sam found a dark door.  he opened it and walked into a room.  he picked up a doll lying on the floor.  the object would soon lead sam to his doom.  the dress of the doll was reddened and wet.   the dark door slammed and the plan was set.

title: Lifeless Tree
author: ashley
text: so i turn to the glass,  i stair at that dark shaded abandoned tree,  and think about my life.  how that tree is leafless and lifeless,  under that dark grey cloud.  i think about how my life is dark and forgotten.  im unable to be loved.  just another girl with a broken heart.  a meaningless life.  with this intence feeling building inside of me,  i stand by that tree.  my arms out.  suddenly,  thought begin to flood my mind.  as i drop down to my knees,  i bury my head in my hands.  uncontrollable tears fall beneath my heart.  mixed emotions,  driving me crazy.  feeling so hurt.  i want to scream.  i just want to run and run til i cant anymore.  i remain hidden under this blanket of darkness.  afraid of the truth.  as i stand,   i look ahead.  i begin to walk.  all i see is a path of darkness.  the more i walk,  the faster i go,  the only light i saw,   so little,  fades to pure black.   darkened.  my heart feels as if its been ripped out of my chest.  this emptiness feeling,  so impossible.  this unbearable pain and my broken heart,  with always remain priceless and hurt.

title: Signs Of Fall
author: ashley
text: the signs of fall,  the wind blows a silent song in the distance birds will call if you think itâ’s spring you are wrong.   leaves change from green to red then down onto the earth they will go itâ’s time for them to go to bed itâ’s getting colder by the day,  you know.   itâ’s cloudy and the rain is pouring down off the moutain the fog will creep hiding the color all around everything is quiet not even a peep.   except for in the distance birds still call these are the signs of fall.

title: Black Heart
author: ashlie
text: do the loved ones in your family know,  have they heard what you have done so? when you killed and demolished peoples lives,  when you took children,  husbands,  and wives?  did you feel regret for what you have done,  seriously,  what reward have you won? did you not even care who they were,  when you threw them around like a sack of fur?  did you slowly slaughter them all,  or go wild and carefree and had a ball? while they trashed and cried out in pain,  did you ever once,  at all,  ever,  wane?  did they cry out in mercy or fear,  when they figured out death was near? did they look in your eyes with fright,  when they knew nothing was all right?  and once you were done,  did you leave,  or stand there for a while and grieve? when you looked at all you had destroyed,  did your black heart remain void?

title: Lost Stars
author: asmah
text: in the end we are only lost stars wandering in the universe, searching for a meaning , shining from outside , dull from inside ,  yet hope shines brighter then the sun , let's hold hands ,  wearing colorful bands , let's walk on moon together , lighter then a feather , what are we?lost stars trying to light up in the dark , never forgetting the essence of our spark , at a dusty park , , who are we ? just a speck of dust within the universe, let's walk somewhere where we can find ourselves ,  because we are only lost stars ,  trying to shine brighter then the sun within dark ,  listening to the birds singing, seeing moon fall asleep , who are we? lost stars trying to accompanying the dark, where are we? lost in the galaxy with other lost stars ,  trying to find ourselves in a huge galaxy , the days are slipping past,  somethings never last , , ,  till the light shines within us let's walk on one strange starry night even if we miss our flight , , ,  remember everything will be alright

title: Shabanu
author: asya
text: â“keep your innermost beauty,  your secrets,  your soul,  hidden far in you heart. â” such was sharmaâ’s wise scheme.  for twas time for shabanu,  a young desert girl,  to become the fourth wife of the wealthy rahim.   yet rahim was not he,  to whom shabanu was promised,  she had hoped to be wed to a cousin,  murad,  still,  the will of her parents shabanu dare not resist,  for this marriageâ’ll cinch safety to her sister,  phulan.   phulan was betrothed to hamir,  muradâ’s brother,  but,  fore to this wedding,  the groom is killed,  itâ’s decided that phulan will be married to murad,   shabanu is sold to rahim,  their fate is sealed.   shabanu is mirthless,  she does not love rahim!   how can she be happy and keep his affection,  she must keep his love,  she must stay his dream or else when he dies,  of his wealth sheâ’ll have not a section.   but sharma is wise; her advice is not dense,  shabanu can keep rahimâ’s love if sheâ’s smart,  she will keep her secrets locked far in a fence,  rahim will reach out,  but never unlock her heart.   note: this poem was written as a book report on the book ''shabanu, '' by suzanne staples.

title: Love
author: barbara
text: if you were sick,  i'd nurse you back to health.  if you were lonely,  i'd keep you company.  if you were sad,  i'd make you happy.  if you needed me,  i'd be there.  id you called me,  i'd come.  if you needed help,  i'd help you.  if you needed love,  i'd love you.  if you were hurt,  i'd be by your side.  i will pray with you and for you.  i will support you in everything you do.  i love you,  i could not imagine the world without you.  i'm lucky to know you and to love you.  i could not imagine living one day without you.  love keeps this world turning round and round.  love is me,  love is you,  love is us together.  love is when i look into your eyes.  love is the magical feeling i get every time i see you.  love is everything,  everything we are,  and everything we do.  love is all around us.  love is just love.

title: Let's become aware now.
author: bhavya
text: today we all close our eyes and have our share of pain,  as we remember all those who were supposed to die in vain.  from hindus to germans to americans to jews,  all were left dead,  who knows if they left a few.   think of the boy who asked his mother where his father was gone,  the mother could only reply somewhere far beyond.  the terrorist attacks took a million of lives,  whether they were children,  or even pregnant wives.   people say they will be useful for india's future.  but where were they all when we were being attacked by foul creatures? we all dream of making our country popular in sports or rock bands,  but when it comes to serve the country,  we all sit down,  with our hand on hand.   helpless people or rich ones with bodyguards,  all affected stayed in the hospital wards.  but were the affected people given any help? no,  whether they scream,  cry or yelp.   someday maybe their souls will rise,  come back to where they left and tell us it was not wise,  no justice no help to the families of the dead,  all was forgotten,  people maybe still crying in their bed.   we all feel as though we serve the country every time,  but we only do so when the wind blows freely and happily in the chime.  when there is trouble,  we run away,  telling people,  'oh,  the minister is gone astray. '  who knows,  someday we might  face an issue like this.  oh someone help me,  we will all wish.  but karma always strikes back,  we will be alone on both happiness and sadness's track.   now let us stop wasting time and become aware,  our life is just like a flare,  our awareness will light up everyone,  but our dullness will sulk everyone.   it is our job,  to light up our country,   not let it become flop,  we have to get it to the top,  let's become aware and never stop.

title: Sonnet for homework.
author: caitlin
text: okay,  sonnet for homework.   i'm in the library ready to write.   my notebook thick pen poised to write on it.   my mind open,  ready to get it right.     my view? the sky,  and billowing white clouds,   tips of tress languidly blowing in the breeze  i cherish the quiet,  the lack of crowds  but the outdoor view is merely a tease.     surrounded by stacks of books,  here i sit.   slight noises of people,  paper and books.   a constant motor's hum and bit by bit  i write this poem,  concerned with how it looks.     does it make sense,  read well,  and does it scan?  or instead,  perhaps,  some trash for the can?

title: My Perfect Love
author: cecelia
text: when i first talked to you,  i didn't know what to say,  but the more we talked,  the more my heart gave away.   but now when i think of you and how you changed my life i can't imagine a day without your light.   you light up my day as if you were the sun you are that sense of my completion,  when my difficult project is done.   you are my strength and my wisdom,  and the keeper of my heart whose grip never weakens,  even where were apart.   i think of you all day,   and dream of you all night,  and every night i wish,  that you could hold me tight.   you are always on my mind,  no matter what time or day even when i shouldn't,  i think of you anyway  and i think this much,  the day seems so long and all the time we spend apart just seems so wrong.   you are my special gift sent from up above sent to me from heaven  sent for to love.   thank you for your smile and your light that fills my dreams you always make it brighter no matter how dark it seems.

title: The Girl
author: cecilia
text: on the top floor of the second story house,  there sat a little  girl who was sitting on her  windowsill.    she was staring out into the  wild,  wild world.  her small  feet dangled in mid air  and the howling wind blew,    her charcoal like mane.  she closed her dark  chocolate eyes and smelled  the windâ’s grassy perfume.    a curve from her pale pink  lips turned into a bright snowy  smile.  she opened her eyes and  the sunâ’s glow made her optics   look like glimmering swimming  pools.  her spectacles made her  eyes bigger and beautiful.   her mind was contemplating   grueling thoughts.  she  had come from a long  journey far away from  where she was sitting.    she had climbed mountains  higher than the tallest trees in the world.  she had pushed  the pressure of words off her   back and swept the anger off  her feet.  she was chained with  despondency and blinded by abhorrence.  but she managed   to crush the metal chains  and shred the blind fold  and walk the path of god.   she stepped into the glaring   light and breathed in hope.   her eyes turned into a waterfall  and fell to the dusty road.  her  journey was like running in a   field of cactus.  she had been  pricked by the cactus and needed  healing.  only she could heal herself,   and she did.  she walked the right   path and let her heart beat and live.    and now she sits on the windowsill  kicking her feet back and forth.   smiling like never before.    sheâ’s an angel with one broken wing and her spirit and love heals it every day.   even though sheâ’s a bull in a china shop  and a toucan,  she is a girl full of faith and life.

title: Passion

text: in the midnight sky the stars are dangling  the moon is shining its softest light  winter is here the purest snow is falling its petals of white to each house each home each life  the street is covered  with midnight dew ice falls deep like pins in the night giving out cold stone hearts to each person nearby  the ice hurt their hearts making warmth of the sun turn to hopeless despair every kindness is washed away to the sky as they melt in the snow still crying  still shivering their life is captured away  in the street of winterâ’s breast of ice captured in the air there  a little girl walked and sang  she danced past thousands of peopleâ’s sorrow eyes deep like the ocean the girlâ’s face glittering with dew    she danced past misery that lay down down down in the darkest heart  she danced past death for hope glowed in her voice she sang sang sang till the echo of her voice let winter itself listen and calmed its treachery  the voice is the voice of an angel? is the voice of peace? or is the voice of christmas bells? no one will ever know  that hidden smile is hope is kindness is the purest sound as it rang summoning the wind to fly with her to learn to feel the sorrow of death of funeral  her hair blazed of golden light shining in the darkest night the night that killed that slaughtered that shattered billion of hearts as they prayed for their beloved ones  even if the snow fell deep winterâ’s fury turns to fire death comes to the air the girlâ’s song of comfort will stay  she sang till the night falls till the sunâ’s light comes  till her voice could not sing the heavy footsteps of death the lightning stroke of hatred could not hide her voice that overwhelming passion that sprang through the highest sky the passion  to sing to die while she sings to give light to everyone here  the girl sang of springâ’s violet flowers of the golden grass of beauty of children playing of the first beam of sunlight  she sang making smells of dandelions scatter through the air making the smile glow on the oneâ’s who are to die making death go away making hope forever stay  then in winterâ’s last roar the sun went up its light shinning golden wings golden laces sprang through the air as they saw the coming back  of their beloved ones marching down the golden pavement  the girl smiled but she couldnâ’t cheer her voice is gone with the sound of the wind  she fell down with every sorrow with that hidden smile with the mouth half opened to sing a tune

title: Building The Boat
author: christopher
text: through so many a puerile swell,  across those beneficial waters of pupilage ingenuity,  my linen heart gave way to an invisible query,  and bloomed esteem for the craft of my fatherâ’s hands.   chafing her underside,  a community of aquatic dunes  were oft meddled,  causing later adulteration of the crystalline depths with cloudy detest,  and in the eyes of every peer burned the crescent pain of souls bereft.   all the days my legs stood naked we rode the waves,  when my skin was still silken enough to feel a rapture so simple,  and mind still tender enough to fear the approaching plunderer,  and when affections of my mother came far before social premeditations.   yet,  her wooden haven had not the strength to preserve youth,  and even as i so desperately tried to rejuvenate such beliefs,  by repeatedly mending port and starboard to a lustrous finish,  time proved a natural draft of all beaded water,  evaporation plaguing my heartâ’s absorption.   my hands grew thick with callous from rowing on all those windless days whereupon the lagoon my thoughts became just as placid,  and from my toils of swift strides across the cerulean cellophane,  came the watching of my cottage shrink away,  when the morning hazes enveloped everything but her and i.   so incredibly hard my father had fashioned her expanse,  from skeleton to decals,  i at length wondered why so much joy his sweaty brow brought him,  and when he painted her red with that meticulous pinstripe of blinding yellow,  i had wondered why he cried as i took her out to sail for the first time.   he had never answered me when i questioned his strange actions,  when many a year thereafter i wondered until a reply to no inquiry he could give,  and,  while grasping the small silken hand of my own son,  returning from my fatherâ’s stone,  i saw in my offspringâ’s eyes the fragility of my shed youth.   though i was unable to maintain my childhood,  that so quickly became the thin sand i often watched slip through my fingers,  perhaps by some means i could relive my bare legs,  through those of my son,  when my life had the future to simply float,  instead of sailing away.

title: An Assemblage of Branches
author: christopher
text: it was but once upon a cold nightâ’s still,  after much a lone and dream trodden path,  that from whence a grove of hesitant mists,  blew forth a soul did the windâ’s chill.   unto my arms she swayed and came to rest,  draping my shoulders in an auburn silk with a slight rustle.  she lay abreast a smooth trunk,  in disturb not to a single dew-soaked blade,  offering her limbs,  i took her hand gently in mine against my chest.   not for a secondâ’s grasp her did i ignore.  softly speaking,  only to be hushed to silence by the windâ’s whisper,  and care i did not for our absence of speech,  but longed with a burning rather to start anew,  and cease my life before.   slowly,  the moon dove into the horizon of coal black.  rooted too i became in a cresting hill of emotion,  planting every seed of my fiber within the soil of her soul,  in trust to be nurtured by that of love given back.   yet,  only once this was,  though through infinity i relive her golden eyes that sparkled and blinked with the windâ’s every motion,  enveloping those of mine with a gaze so true as to be none other that that of love.  but my roots by daylight where unearthed,  for this was not what she had to give.   her soul had been from but a mists cruel deceived,  and heart she had none,  so carved her one i did,  with lone initials i dug,  cutting through bark in search of skin.  now with the organ she was,  but without the spark of life i had so deeply believed.   her eyes of the moonlight were no more,  the sun she preferred to that of me and nightly care.  again the breeze came and took her leaves elsewhere,  for with but another to share,  when it should have been i carried aloft a cool zephyr--for i--and i alone knew true love.  i think perhaps she wasnâ’t alive at all,  but merely an assemblage of branches swaying in the night air.

title: Fishers of Men
author: christopher
text: moisture robbed sand,  drilled with thirsty holes,  amphibious jetties play tug of war with land and sea.  the sunken eyes of the fisherman stare expressionless at rhythmic waves.   lines remain limp,  inert.  knives in their sheaths lacking the desired red tinge,   today the sea air flows easily through the nets.   into the black aqua abyss lures dive deep,  seeking a meaty treasure wrapped in paper thin diamonds,  the fish avoid capture.   the assumed marine life of little intellect the rubber flinchers,  they gain a foothold,  outsmarting the man convinced he was the victor.   have the tables turned on life and through a pair of frightened goggle eyes,  you would gain an understanding of a blurry,  rippled innocence.   and now like the prey you have become,  your demise dependent on the extremity of your gullible mind,  slowly,  the fish get the better of the fisherman.   to our avail for once not,  the fish load us up in buckets,  boxes and cans,  packed hard we are in greedâ’s icy chill.   for our stilted actions we shall pay,  and off the rocks we fall and plunge into the cold wetness,  a transition more than suitable takes place.   the rays of light diminish,  like the quality of our life,  the world before,  forever gone,  like the fish,  sadly,  we have become.   eternally we are destined to swim in a sea of man-made irony,  until caught by the hook of our own.

title: War on Parkwood
author: christopher
text: war on parkwood    devout catholicism lowered the crucifix from above the headboard,  penning sworn morality across pressed white cotton that sent three corduroy-clad soldiers  marching abroad a stark womb.  down parkwood,  armed with the cork gun debauchers  of naã¯ve psyches who left clean hands adrift dirty gutters---trenches,  clasping wooden replicas all sodden with water---blood.  to be demoted by red plasticity; five-ringed  and chamber housed,   serving as ammo in play of their war on parkwood.  when daylight colored palms black,  straining spirits through slotted greenery,  to dawn certainty not,  whether the faint note upon their ear was cap gun backwash---or a bullets whisper.  that so often became  muffled in flesh---and foliage,   dwarfed by vietnamâ’s tangled masses---or koreaâ’s.  like their mothers hair protruding from clenched hands,  her knuckles white---veins so very red; as a balled apron absorbs her catholicism,  for prayers proved reaper of none  but the anguish---and guilt. \t that their father cynically suppresses,  though he finds himself in daily confession in attempts to whitewash  the memory of letting his boys  take the rifle out back and discharge shells---unthinking,  through a white paper target---truce flag upheld.  broaching some foreign heart to bear blood,  their own  just as red.    copyright 2002 christopher h.

title: The Cliff of Doom
author: christopher
text: there we were,  standing at the bottom of one of the biggest cliffs  we would climb.   it seemed to go on forever,  colder as we climbed,  cold,  hard,  solid face of the cliff.  we could hear the people cheer,   as we went higher,  up the jagged,  sharp,  hard,  part of the cliff.   we could hear the people cheer,  as we went higher up the  jagged,  sharp,  hard,  part of the cliff.     â“come on,  you can do it. â” we could hear the tiny looking people say.  the wind blew hard and cold,  it got harder to breath,  â“i canâ’t go any fartherâ”  said my trusty and faithful cousin j. c.  â‘ â‘â’ we have to. â’â’ i said.  so as we got closer to our destination,   i felt weak,  and cripple! then all of a sudden,   my legs gave out from under me.  i started to slide,  i went down hard and fast,  â‘â’holy crapâ’â’!  my cousin yelled.  the crowed started to  scream,  as i slid farther from where  i was meant to go.   then all of a sudden,  i felt something  grab ahold of my wrist.   i looked up and saw jc holding  on to the cliff and my wrist.  â“your not going to leave my up here  alone. â’â’ he said.  â‘â’ i wasâ’nt planing on it. â’â’ i said.  so he pulled me back up and ew wrestled the cliff  together.  we picked up the pace.   i could hear the crowed  cheer as we started to climb once more.  we were covering more ground this time.  the crowed at the bottom was cheering and gathering others to watch the great excitement.  we made it,  we reach our goal.   we stood on the toplooking ta all the bottom.  we still remember the cliffs of doom.

title: When I ThinkOf You
author: christy
text: it is a cloudy day.  i can not help but think of you.  the clouds are plentiful.  they hold in their rain.  much like how thoughts of you are abundant,  yet i still hold back my tears.  occasionally,  the cloud can not help but spill.  it is only natural.  tears run down my face,  on occasion.  it is only normal.   seasons change.  weather changes.  and i will think of you.  clouds keep moving forward,  but their mark never leaves.  i can not undo how you have changed me.  one never completely forgets who they truly love,  but is more careful the next time outside.   i will look up at the sky,  and smile.  the sun will shine as bright as before.  i will never forget you.  clouds move on,  but the sky never forgets them.  as once,  i was happy to have you in my life.  i will just make sure to bring sunscreen or an umbrella next time.   it will be a new season,  but the last is never forgotten.  and so,  i'll think of you.   does one forget summer's shining,  or learn to appreciate autumn's breeze?  you.  it is you i will think of on a cloudy day.

title: I Am...
author: cindy
text: i am a curious girl that doesn't know what she wants.  i wonder if i'll still be friends with people later on in life.  i hear someone breathing and it bounces off the walls of the small blue room.  i see people hurting others in this crazy world.  i want to know what i want! i am a curious girl that doesn't know what she wants.   i pretend to be a different person than i really am.  i feel locked up in a room and i can't get out.  i touch the walls of the room,  hoping to open some kind of door.  i worry that i will never get out of the room.  i cry alone in the room,  hoping someone will hear me.  i am a curious girl that doesn't know what she wants.   i understand there are ways that i can change.  i say to myself,  everything will turn out great.  i dream of being happy with someone i love.  i try to make myself believe everything is okay now.  i hope i will be happy and everything will work out as planned.  i am a curious girl that doesn't know what she wants.

title: My Rose
author: cody
text: my rose  you.  you are my rose,  perfect in every way.  with a fragrance unmatched by any other,  skin soft as a petal,  blooming into a beautiful flower.  vulnerable,  you hide,  protecting yourself with thorns,  so none may steal your beauty.  your eyes infinitely deep,  filled with wonder and love.  lips so red,  so soft,  only a king is deserving.  and you will be his queen,  given the highest treasures,  in hope you will love the king.  you are no mere picture,  for it would take more than a thousand words to start describing your beauty alone.  you are different and distant,  i reach out but cannot touch,  for you must not be tainted.  you are different and distant,  yet you are close and familiar.  i see you very little,  but when you are to be seen,  i light up like a candle,  i hate watching you go,   seeing you leave blows out my candle.  parting is such sweet sorrow,  but i will count the seconds until you are to be seen once more.  you were picked from a group where all are the same,  yet somehow you are ultimately unique your blinding beauty hits,  and the perfect words canâ’t begin to describe.  more precious than gold,  you are to me.  unforgettable,  etched in memory,  you dazzle me,  day-in,  day-out,  you cease to fail.  you.  you are my rose.

title: Music
author: daniel
text: it has a pulse  a tempo to be precise.  living and breathing  all day and night.   it's mood can be sorrow or joyous in many ways.  it can stop or go what can i say.   it speaks through dynamics moving at different speeds.  never does one know when it might be complete.   it's made of many notes rhythmically arranged.  always expressing thoughts sometimes making quotes.   it accents by loudness it smooths through ties.  every staff is broken by bar lines.   it causes one to think  and opens memories.  it makes the mind imagine many,  many,  things!  this is what i call music!
