title: Her Heart.
author: dellene
text: her heart once loved,  her heart once happy,  her heart once hoping,  her heart once filled with faith,   her heart left in pieces,  her heart left cold,  her heart left in darkness,  her heart left in pain her heart left in blood,  her heart left faithless,  her heart left hopeless,  her heart left without love,  her heart left broken,   her heart grew strong,  her heart grew cold,  her heart grew walls,  her heart grew in focus,  her heart grew resistance,  her heart grew emptiness,  her heart grew hatred,   her heart still in pain,  her heart still bleeding,  her heart still dying,  for many years,    a thousand hearts she broken,  a thousand hearts she resisted,  a thousand hearts she sent away,  a thousand hearts she trashed,  a thousand hearts she ripped out,  a thousand hearts she gave false hope,  a thousand times she thought of her once loved heart so left in pieces,  a thousand times she kept it against every man,   a single heart,  a single smile,  a single soul,  a single touch,   left her melting,  left her wanting more,  left her paralyzed,  left her in love once again,   a fool she was,  a fool she is,  a fool she still is,   for love once again left her blind,  left her inlove,  left her wanting more,   her mind was seeing what her heart did not,  her mind was warning her to stay away,  her mind was saying get away,  her mind was saying don't fool yourself,   her heart was not listening,  her heart was blind,  her heart wanting more by the second,  her heart would not let pain get in the way,   yet things got bad,  her heart is breaking,  her heart saying i should've listen,  her heart still not able to say goodbye,  her heart keeps breaking,  her heart keeps bleeding,  her heart keeps seeing more and more,   her heart fell for another heart,  her heart fell for another fool,  her heart fell for a heart she loves too much,  her heart fell for a heart she is unable to leave,   her heart will cause her pain,  her heart will cause her fear,  her heart will cause her darkness,  her heart will cause her emptiness,  her heart will cause her blood,  her heart will cause her death,   her heart will die loving one heart,  her heart will title: A Mother.
author: dellene
text:
all my life i have been wondering,   wondering what a guardian angel look like,   wondering if i have a guardian angel,   wondering who is making sure i am safe,    i have prayed and ask god to show me,   never being able to understand why he doesn't,   always thinking that i do not have a guardian angel.  .  .  .    till now,   up until today i thought that i do not have one,   as i lay upon my bed it just came to me,   mom you are my guardian angel,   you have always been my guardian angel,   watching over me!   you are the one that took care of me,   when i cry you cried with me,   when a fell you picked me up and patched it up,   after words you will kiss the bruise,   say that its alright to cry,   you have thought me how to become a woman,   you called when i was not home,   making sure a am safe,   when i was in panic you made it alright.  .  .  .    mom my list could go on and on its a never ending list of thing you as my guardian angel did and still does do for me.  .  .    mom there is nothing in this world that could say nor show how much it all means to me,   how much i appreciate it,   mom i can only say that i love you with all my heart!  <b< /p=\>

title: Brilliant Whit Birch Trees
author: dylan
text: dylan m october 28,  2008 english 9,  b2  brilliant white birch trees: discovering the scientific method on water day  \tas i walked to the bus from my front door,  i looked at the light gray,  foreboding sky.   that day was water day,  a day that we would be spending outside at school,  and our teachers could not have picked a better day to represent an example of precipitation in the water cycle.   once on the bus,  i noticed the condensation on the windows,  and wondered if we would be taught about how over-saturated moisture in the air causes the big beads of water on flat surfaces.   as it turned out,  what we learned in each class paralleled the steps of the scientific method.    \tthe first step in the scientific method is gathering data.   coincidentally,  the first assignment i had that day was to gather evidence and ideas.   the procedure went as follows: walk on a path through the woods,  keep journal open and write down everything you notice,  find objects that would inspire creative thinking,  then write that down and bring all the ideas together.   the most memorable piece of evidence that i found was a piece of birch bark.   simple and insignificant in itself,  it triggers memories of that day for me.   i remember looking across the desolate field at the forest and noticing the birch trees.   with the fall leavesâ’ vibrant colors and the monochrome gray sky,  the white birch trees suddenly expressed themselves in a way like never before.   their skinny,  soft forms became strong with simple white color.   the white was so much more intense than the brown of the more powerful hard trees.   i went away from this experience changed,  both literally and mentally.   literally,  because i was more damp than before i ventured outside.   mentally,  because i will never forget the bright white of those birch trees.    \tmeasuring and organizing data is another part of the scientific method and this step was represented by our second activity of the day.   representatives from poland springs taught the class about the area and environment around a river.   we attached a number to everything we could,  which is a part of scientific data organization.   what is the temperature in the air?  how many deciduous and coniferous trees are there?  what types of grasses are in the area?  all these pieces of information were organized and summarized into a final product that could help a scientist determine the ecosystem encompassing the riverbank.  i left this class slightly confused; i donâ’t think i really understood the purpose of the measurements.   data must be compiled and given some meaning later in the process.    \tthe final part of the scientific method must incorporate everything that has been shown,  just like a math equation.   by calculating the speed,  depth and area of the river,  the class determined the final result of gallons per minute.   i feel i really understand the practical application of equations now.   the fact that someone can produce an answer for a tough question simply by measuring a few things and bringing the information together is astounding.   previously,  i had only done math to complete the assignment,  now i have discovered a new concept and solved a real problem with math.   the key component in almost every math problem is finding information,  and bringing the information together in a way that makes sense to solve the problem,  just as we did throughout the dayâ’s activities.    \tthe bus ride home for me is similar to the conclusion of a lab report,  in which i try to explain to myself what actually happened.   i stare out the droplet covered window,  still noticing the birch trees,  and think about the day i had experienced.   this is the time when i make the connections between the math,  english and science of the day.   i realized that water day was more than just a break in the monotonous school routine,  it was also a way of putting a message across:  the answer is always right where youâ’re looking,  you just have to bring all the details and problems together in order to find the answer.

title: Barns and Alleys
author: ed
text: a boy sits in a chair with nothing to write,  yet he continues to scribble on throughout the night.  his pen flies an endless flight,  his mind filled with horror; fright.  his brain fights an endless fight.  left hand steady as a kite; right hand filled with a pain that bites.  over his vision crawl the mites.  brain making a new constitution with rights that constricts his heart quite tight.  will there be an end to this plight? will this stop at any height? will his death be caused by something so slight? will his skin become chalk white? while he sits in a chair with nothing to write; while he scribbles on throughout the night.

title: Untitled
author: ed
text: there is a ticking that is only to be heard at night.  when the slightest beams of sun are gone from sight.  a ticking that tocks a hollow clock sound of plight.   it is a ticking that comes from deep in your soul.  it means you are living; your life is on a roll; your gears are grinding; revolving their knobby knolls.   it is a clock,  but you cannot read it and see when it ends; when you will cease to be.   sometimes,  when you are sad,  the ticking sound can drive you mad.  sometimes,  when you are young,  the ticking has a forkã©d tongue.  sometimes,  when you are old,  the ticking talks of ending cold.   just remember,  when the ticking scares your heart into flips and flops,  there is a much more horrid part: when the ticking stops.

title: Nicotine Dreams

title: Untitled
author: ed
text: the dark.  when the sun is pulled below the horizon by an unseen hand called time,  black liquid floods the forrest.  shadows begin to leak and grow.  nightmares slither,  not many at first,  then pour outward from large aquaducts construsted of blocks from our imagination.   the dark.  night falls and whispers unreason into our ears.  with a cape drawn and the visual world hidden from view,  a new evil dawns evil in our brains.  screams erupt from mouths we didn't know we had.  terror sinks teeths coated with poison and hallucinatory germs into our main blood streams.  a cold nose,  freezing,  pokes at our souls and inhales.  fear marks it's territory with fright inducing urine.   the dawn.  it sears the horrors with fire,  causing retreat,  but not extermination.  the dawn encourages self scrutiny,  reprimandation.  the shadows recede.

title: Taoism
author: ed
text: the sailboats in the oceans were full of emotion,  sailing the seven seas.   five they were,  always racing,  in a hurry,  always hasting,  sailing the seven seas.   never did the other creatures boss them,  trying not to cross them,  only the sea,  it dared to toss them,  â‘round the seven seas.   one day,  a half blind old whale,  a bluish type of pale,   surfaced by the sails,   in the stormy seven seas.   then happened the collision made with unknown precision.  producing a rudderless boat,  which luck kept afloat.  and died the whale in the seven seas.   the four laughed at their comrade there,  seeing hilarity without care.  then fell the rudderless boat asleep,  in a depression,  ever deep.  amidst the roaring of the seven seas.   the boat awakened to a crash,  confused as to what caused that smash.  the sailboatâ’s depression thinned as he noticed that the wind pushed him with a speed that sinned,  without a rudder to slow him against the seven seas.   that day the boat sailed many miles,  and wore a very many smiles.  he took notice of all the gulls,  and the dolphins at his hulls,  so about all this he mulled,  while sailing the seven seas.   with the day at itâ’s end he met his old friends,  but soon they werenâ’t there.  but he didnâ’t mind (now the wind was his guide. ) so he sailed on the air,  over the fair seven seas.

title: The Carousel
author: ed
text: i stand in line with everybody else.  i see the monster,  but iâ’m not scared (iâ’ve seen him before).  he has light brown skin,  curling horns,  and a tired face.  he looks at me.  â“get on, â” he replies,  even though i didnâ’t say anything.  there are several horses.  they all have gruesome expressions on their faces.  expressions of pain,  fear,  and confusion.  they have different names.  self-pity.  guilt.  acceptance.  denial.  i mount self-pity.  itâ’s closest to me.  it always has a pretty smooth ride.  gears grind.  my own thoughts pour from the speakers like corny music.  i paid for my ticket,  now i have to use it as i go around.  and around.

title: Life
author: elizabeth
text: how do you live your life? mine is a day by day step,   but becareful you might  fall,  mess up,  die.  all i worry about is how long i'll live.  will i have  children,  grandchildren? will i live to see tomorrow? what is happening? all  i used to care about  was friends,  clothes,   church,  school,  relationships.  now i think of how my life will end.  will i be saved and go to heaven or will i  die and be sent to  hell for all eternity? will i die in a car wreck,  a shooting,  a gang? what will happen to my  family? what is going  on in my head? am i  losing my mind? no,  i'm  preparing my life for  what might happen in the near future.  so what will your life end like? mine,  i don't know,  but i'm working on  fixing it right now.  can you say when  you'll die,  where you'll die,  and why? i think not,  so prepare now  for the end.  what will your life be?

title: Choices
author: elizabeth
text: everyday people have choices to make.  do you make any? if so,  are they important to you? i think so.  people make choices of what to eat,  where  to sleep,  who to be  with,  and most important of all do they want to  live.  another choice is  to believe in christ or not.  choices are hard for me,  especially during the rough times.  i wonder why i'm  alive.  i think why  am i here,  can i leave,   and is that possible. all i know is i'm here for a reason so i  won't take my own  life,  but i want help to find my purpose here on earth.  so watch for your choices and make the right ones.  i know  i sure hope i do.

title: Hate, or love?
author: emily
text: he makes me want him,  yet i hate him.  he breathes death upon me,  yet all i think of is him.  tempting me to love him,  then ruining me when i do,  is he real,  or just a mirage? regret,  confusion,  hating him,  then loving him.  helpless to anything but love.  saying that i hate him,  knowing that i don't.  haunted and unhappy,  same routine every day.  thoughts of release from his spell,  yet nothing happens.  nothing shows on the outside,  but that i am,  a victim of his stare.

title: Pain
author: emily
text: i'm so hollow,  gouged out inside,  nothing left,  i can't feel anything.  when i scream,   no one hears,  not even me.  there's nothing inside.  whatever is left is nothing but a  nightmare.  no voice,  no thoughts,  no soul.  is this pain? because i don't feel anything.  it's so numb.

title: Alone
author: emily
text: no one hears me,  i'm screaming,  crying,  pleading,  falling.  down and down and down.  into a pool of darkness,   not a single crack of light.  the night air around me,  quiet,  truthful,  silent.  rage,  pain,  hatred,  all squeezed inside,   with nowhere to go.  someday soon,  it will all come out,  the secrets,  the tears,  the screams,  the cries,   with no one to hear.  alone.

title: Mask
author: emily
text: i look into the mirror,  seeing nothing.  what's there? why am i hidden? behind a mask.  all i see is a mask,  betraying nothing,  hiding everything.  perfect in every detail,  no flaws,  yet no emotion shows.  look into the eyes,  the pools of darkness.  what do you see? is there a mask there too?

title: You
author: emily
text: so involved in yourself,  can't hear my cries,  my anguish,  my tears.  i scream,  and you stand there doing nothing.  what do you hear? i'm screaming,  bleeding,  crying,  yet you just laugh.  what are you laughing at? i'm drowning,  dying,  praying,  but you don't even flinch.  so wrapped up in your own little battles,  that you don't notice my war.  you were once my lover,  but now i don't even know you.

title: When I Awoke One Morning
author: emily
text: when i awoke one morning,  i felt the cool breeze coming in from my window.  i went outside to get the paper and i felt the warm sun shining on me.  i felt like i was the only person in the world but yet i saw the kids playing across the street.  i soon realized i'm the happiest i've ever been and i like it that way.

title: Your heart is in his hands.
author: erica
text: his smile makes you weak in the knees.  his touch makes you feel safe.  he's a blanket of warmth that you refuse to share.  he holds your heart in his hands,  but his is to hard to find.  you look and coax,  but each time he slips away with an excuse,  not brave enough to trust himself in your hand.  he is unpredictable he's there only for a moment then gone,  you wish to kill all in your path and shun away all those who try to help.  ''steal your heart away,  for it was taken from you in vain!'' your friends say.  you cannot,  you want the pain to stop.  against your will,  your heart will not give up.  you know deep down the only way to not live your life in regret is to ''follow your heart'' where ever it leads you.  it won't lead you wrong.  in the end,  he may grow older and sneak his way into your waiting arms.  hoping your waiting hands will still love.

title: The Day the Paintbrush Slipped
author: freya-jean
text: no one knew,  they didn't care to see.  the one who was dying,  very quietly.   they didn't know red was the colour,  she wanted to see.  or that she was very slowly,  dying inside.  they didn't know how she felt,  with all the darkness she would hide.   her mind lead her,  to do some scary things.  she didn't know where to turn,  but to see what the devil brings.   she was a very skilled artist,  by day she sang,  but by night she would paint.  she would paint all night long,  until she would finally faint.   her pictures were red,  but were hidden away,  her smile hid the pain,  that she felt each day.   then one day her paintbrush slipped,  blood red paint covered the floor.  no one knew what happened,  when they finally saw.   that this girl was lost,  and needed to feel.  so she decided to feel pain,  to know that she is real.  so she only knew pain,  but no one could ever see,  as her walls kept her hidden away,  so we could never see her scars,  until that day.  the day that the paintbrush slipped,  and she was taken away,  to land were she is safe and free,  but forever scarred and grieving were her family.

title: Wonder
author: gary
text: wonder  when i hold you in my arms,  before you drift to sleep,  i stroke your golden hair,  and place a loving kiss,  on your tender cheek,  and you wonder why i love you,  only i canâ’t explain,  there has to be something,  to make me feel the way i do,  when iâ’m next to you.   iâ’m sitting here wondering about you,  why do you come around me? instead of hanging out with your popular friends,  but youâ’re here sitting next to me,  when no one else will,  and i wonder why you love me,  only you canâ’t explain,  there has to be something,  to make you feel the way you do,  when youâ’re next to me.   you wake up and iâ’m still right there,  you smile with that look in your eyes,  that look says your content with me,  i give you a gentle kiss on your brow,  then we get up and leave,  and we wonder why we love each other,  only we canâ’t explain,  there has to be something,  to make us feel the way we do,  when weâ’re together.

title: Tiny Star
author: gianna
text: shade me with patience,  tiny star.  though,  i can't perceive you're age; opal white with youth or chrome yellow with wisdom.  you could be a member of ordion's belt or the main event of the big dipper.  orbit between the depths of the asteroid belt to find sacred endurance.  promise me that with whatever viewing point i wish upon you from,  you'll be my alley.  for,  march is too gelid and spring is a snoozing,  lazy mockingbird.  shade me with patience,  tiny star.   paint me with diversity,  tiny star.  my dopplegangers seem to show me up every which way.  your dandeling flares with phoenix spunk creep your body effortlessly.  one a polar opposite from the next,  and so on,  and so on.  they are your inferno snowflakes.  send me your creativity,  for i yearn to be original.  paint me with diversity,  tiny star.   blanket me with courtesy,  tiny star.  you are my kindness rolemodel.  you are keen to welcome 1000 suns into your orbit.  you and your neighbors toast with drops of the milkyway.  for,  i haven't got a sufficient amount of rest and the forecast couldn't frustrate me further.  for,  my little cousins deserve the nicest of actions.  blanket me with courtesy,  tiny star.   bless me with sleep,  tiny star.  when time and space lock down for the night,  your dream-filled radiance wouldn't and couldn't gleam brighter.  though,  that doesn't distract you from your z's.  you've had more productive days.  you've had less productive days.  productive days of permitting my daily needs.  for,  i have told you all my desires for the evening.  bless me with sleep,  tiny star.

text: tiny falsehoods,  they flow together.  growing,  emerging into,  the ocean that that seems to keep on going it sucks you in,  flowing quickly each wave a measure of happiness growing larger as they head towards shore  a journey that can overcome the truth quickly speeding like the beat of your heart except your heart slows before you die and this river turns to a waterfall of hate flinging you over the edge suddenly with out warning.

title: This Life, This World
author: jeniffer
text: blissful morning stars loom at the sky.  ancient grief wears away.  i am close by.   tears stream from clouds,  all this gives me fear to speak aloud.   the nerves tighten at my spine.  my muscles ache for respite,  as i look at the dawn sky.   my walk to eternity will be rewarded.  i only fear that i wear away before it is done.  all my life's things have been grounded.   i crawl the last stretch of the game.  bay of life is near,  my life's aim.   a last,  i dive into the pool.  of long tiresome mind,  i am rid.  surrounds me does awakening cool.   fear not the temptation of earth,  i am above it now,  away from the treacherous hearth.   heed my word,  my voice.  time is done,  make your choice.   fall not back into the pit,  take my outstretched hand.  come to the promise land.   voices speak unknown words.  i feel sorrow for those who show broken promises like feathers of birds.   i have no choice do i.  may it be so,  it must be done.  don't with anger to me cry.

title: Unconditional Love
author: jennie
text: unconditional love  he,  teddy,  my fickle little bear,  his glassy eyes and soft fur fill me with happiness,  when he sleeps you can do nothing but smile.   when awake he is loving yet fickle.  his fragile body,  his rabbit like back paws.  he rolls over onto his back,  and looks up at me adoringly and purrs.  he has pure love in his golden yellow eyes,  unconditional love.

title: To Me YouÂ’re Everything
author: jennifer
text: it's times like these when your here kissing me nothing makes sense i only know that we're meant to be  tightly wrapped up in your love i feel so warm and protected to hateful thoughts and jealous words i remain unaffected  i've been to hell and back but i don't remember the journey nothing matters anymore except that you love me  the simple thought of you  makes my sorrow fade away i lock up my past depression and save it for another day  looking into your eyes you're the key to my heart finally i realize you're my light in the dark  you pull me through the blackness you able me to fly with broken wings you brighten up my shadowed soul  and show me greater things  life can be unbearable sometimes things are pretty rough i was once searching for a cure now your love is more than enough  i love you the truest words i'll ever say nothing or anyone could ever make me feel a different way  i need nothing but you i live off the happiness you bring a feeling so strong i know it canâ’t be wrong to me you're everything.

title: ''Love is Powerful''
author: jeriesha
text: love is a powerful feeling.  love can be as sweet as pink petals.  but love can also be sour as a green apple.  when your in love it can be the most wonderful feeling in the world.  your always thinking of that certain person that makes you feel special,  like your the only person in the world.  love can overpower you.  love is beyond your reach.  love can control every vain in your body.  love drives you to do cruel things.  when the love of your life no longer loves you, you would do anything to win him back.  you can't fight back the tears.  you can't fight back the painful feeling.  you are left with a cold broken heart, a feeling that will never go away.  love is deep.  love is me.  love is powerful.

title: ''Who Am I''

title: ''Love Hurts''
author: jeriesha
text: what do i do? am tired of feeling this way.  my heart beats everyday thinking of you,  wanting you to come back to me.  you meant everything to me,  but it hurts knowing i meant nothing to you.  you was my love.  i am lost in this world and don't know what to do.  a dream about you every night hoping you will come back to me.  but you love someone else now.  and nothing i say or do will bring you back.  i didn't want to loose you, but i realize that i lost you forever.

title: ''Hide In the Shadows''

text: i want to hide on the dark shadows.  i want to be alone will no one can find me.  everyday i feel hurt, sad, and depressed.  i feel like i have no one to turn to.  i want to hide in the dark shadows.  i don't want to feel anymore pain.  all this is too much for me, too overwhelming.  i feel like am going to explode any minute.  things are never go to get better.  and so i want to hide myself in the dark shadows.

title: I Have A Dream
author: jessica
text: i have a dream everyone will be free,  i have a dream they'll be led to what they want to be.  i have a dream that the killing will stop,  i have a dream there will be no more gun shots.  i have a dream that the hungry and homeless won't have to suffer anymore,  i have a dream that they won't be ignored.  i have a dream that we won't have to fight amongst each other,  i have a dream that one day we'll start acting like sisters and brothers.  i have a dream that the african-americans who fought for our freedom can see how our world has changed,  and to know that something's are not the same.  i have a dream that you and i can take each others hand and let everyone see,  that we're living in a world of peace and harmony.  i have a dream children can get the education that they need,  i have a dream that they'll get it and suceed.  i have a dream we won't be judged from the outside,  but that people would take a deeper look inside.  i have a dream that people will keep their strength,  courage,  and pride and never let it slip away,  i have a dream that this world would come together as one someday.

title: Live on
author: jessica
text: am i still here? yes! god bless me.  i live on another day.  i live on to cry when i hurt.  i hurt when you turn you back.  my back against the world for you.  the world a dark cruel place we live on.  yet i mange to live on.   i see you,  yet i'm blind.  i'm blind by your love.  your love that is not good for me.  no good for me,  so i roll up to die.  i roll up to die,  yet i'm  still  here.  i live on to look at you in your face  and say ''i'm no dead yet!'' i live on

title: The Two Sides To Love
author: jessica
text: but love is not so easy,  now is it? the thought of he loves you,  loves you not kills.  wishing you can make the feeling omit.  just the you realize you love the thrills.   rain with love pours down and flowers follow.  you hope that the rainfall lasts forever.  then a thunderstorm rolls over and so,  things change once more it's not quite that clever.   we all want things we can't have,  love is one.  hardship makes up love,  so why want it now? love comes,  but you won't know yet it's begun.  weirdly enough,  falls upon us somehow.   love is tough,  yet we all want it right now.  we take the time to find the one,  but how?

title: Always
author: jessica
text: you see me standing there with tears coming down my face not knowing what was happening,  with my mind completely out in space i try and zone back into reality letting myself go all in out; all in free i don't know what else i can do but sit here and cry thinking about all times we've had,  wishing i was the one who had died all our happy and sad good and bad your body is all empty and cold maybe not now,  but soon your body will be old you were so young one thing i will always remember that you said you always told me to never look behind me and always to look ahead now that you're gone,  where no one can see your face i promise you now,  you're in my heart directly in a better place.

title: Beneath
author: jessica
text: think of the petals on a rose so soft to touch.  a feeling just like that should make you want so much.  you see it's beauty and like the smell unlike me.  i see it's thorns and that it withers eventually.  there should be more behind what we see everyday.  something we think so tiny could have so much to say.  we have no right to sit and assume we have knowledge from first sight.  we fool ourselves and hide our emotions; are we so afraid of fright? look beyond and beneath next time you think you ''know. '' i'd hate to be the one to come back and say ''i told you so. ''

title: September
author: jimmy
text: september i love to go out in late september.  not to hot and not too cold,  just right like goldilocks.  if heaven felt like anything it would be this,  pure bliss.  leaves start to change,  but not fall.   blend of yellow and green  looks like a desert oasis.  smells nice,  no pollution,   no ice,  just clean.   it makes you reminisce about the good times.  those sad thoughts can wait a day,  or for a rainy day but now it's pure bliss the days you will remember forever.

title: Smoke

text: smoke they taste good to her  but not exactly,  its pretty nasty.  it's something ignored.  she sparks a cigarette,  the fire ignited slowly burns,  the smoke fills then lingers in her lungs.  it returns just as toxic doing second hand damage.   â“why canâ’t i stop?â” she asks  â“i have asthma,  my kids do tooâ”  i don't like any of this ,  no one around me does either.  whenever i put you down,   you come back up,  whenever i toss you,  you come right back,  my habits canâ’t quit themselves.   so now i'm burying you,  under my foot,  now what we had is ashes.   only if it were that easy,  to leave the demons that reside in my being.

title: The Lamppost I So Often Ignore
author: john
text: for oft when on a dreary street i walk,   and the breath of the night catching up behind me,   i stop to tilt my head at the specks of light above,   wondering how they could be so lovely.   but at the edge of my watery eye there seems to be  something emanating enchantments of a variety  soothing my soul,  warming my skin,   piercing through my sturdy bones  for once,  i thought of how long a journey iâ’ve been through  encompassing all limits,  beating lifeâ’s odds,   embracing all the infinite chances  and for a split second i realized what i would be  if god,  the almighty wouldnâ’t have been guiding me.   this sudden realization i so often neglect  as i pass by that familiar light.   the light that guides me all the way,   safe,  unharmed to where i home.   i strode closer to the light as ever before  alas! a rusty lamppost outshines specks of all,   the lamppost i so often ignore.

title: Fear

title: The Little Blue Table
author: jordan
text: sitting at the little blue table,  drinking my heated chocolate milk,  not having to worry about a thing.  mornings spent eating,  playing,  and spilling on the little blue table,  the memories.  the leathery feel of the little blue table,  legs that wobble with fear from those around.  the little blue table,  strong,  yet aging,   with legs that can cut you if you shake it.  the legs of the little blue table,  metal that shines through the blue paint,  shaky legs,  old bruises.  time will fly by you,  things will grow and age,   the little blue table,  a strong,  old capsule that will fall.  my knees hit the table now,  this shaky table will lead to an avalanche of things.  the days shorter,  work longer,  spilt,  warm milk that i grow tired of.  my admiration for the little blue table will never fade,   passing and going once in a while.  tiring days,  wonderful memories,  the little blue table.

title: Fishing Trip
author: jordyn
text: i went on a fishing trip today.  yes sir i did.   we got in the middle of the pond,  stopped the boat,  and worm got me ready to bait.   he opened my mouth,  he put the hook in and he tightened it in.  sighing,  he threw the line behind him and threw me in the water.   as i sailed through the air,  i saw the worm lounging back and relaxing.   hitting the water with a splash! i fell under,  the coldness of the water rushing up to great me.   i settled in the middle,  underwater and gave a sigh,  waiting for my friend.   ------------splash!-----------  i looked around and saw another human.   hi!  hi!  after out conversation,  i fell asleep.   wakening up cause a sudden school of fish had flown by me,  i looked up and saw a great big fish advancing toward me.  knowing the fish was the right size for the worm,  i stood perfectly still.   aaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaahhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhh!!!!!!!!  i screamed as the fish swallowed me whole.   now my worm has a new fish and i have a new home.   lighter anyone?

title: This is me

title: Enchanted
author: juwayriya
text: if i could go to a place i wish,  a place that does not exist.   a place where you don't have to worry about how you dress,  or one where you'll have no stress.  a place where you don't have to worry about worldly things.  but one that you see in your most extraordinary dreams.  with the best of nature and glistening streams,  lay rocks and pebbles in its way,  all in shades of black, blue and gray.  the alluring aroma of the beautiful flowers,  would make you feel just the way you are.  the warm morn sunlight peeps through the evergreen trees,  as if the showers had just poured to keep it fresh and green.   the beauty of the morning dew on the leaves,   took away all of your griefs.   you find yourself standing amidst the forest,  in the most beautiful robe,  white in hue.  mezmerized by this heart warming panoramic view.  there is something extraordinary about this forest,  that catches your interest .  you always feel like being looked over and not alone.  just as you were figuring this out, a creature appeared, rolling out of the thickets, and for heaven's sake! it was a gnome! he had ears like elves,  and he was so short he could barely reach the lowest shelf.  with a long pointy red hat and a long white beard.  a nose so red as if it had been severed.  you backed up slightly thinking it was dangerous.   just when it smiled a smile , so gregarious,   all the other creatures came out of their hide, like a signal the gnome gave them to say,  harm is out of the way.  you couldn't believe your eyes when you saw,  pixies and fairies disguised as calla.  milky white unicorns,  with emeralds in their horns.  elves, mermaids,  will 'o' the wisps, glow birds, dwarves , hippogriffs,  and trolls covered in sparkling mist.  they seemed rather friendly, cheerful and made the best of entertainers .  not like the ones you see in this world , full of refrainers.   you danced, singed and laughed to your heart's content.   seemed like it was the best day of your life,  just when the sun began to set , it was time for you to leave and you sighed,  you wanted to stay there forever,  but you had no choice.  for you had to go back to the real world,   the one filled with monsters and dreadful lies.

title: Ringbearer

title: Whisper Infinity

text: there is a black hole heading toward my face.  it is as dark as cole making no sign or trace.  but clearly you can see that there is something inside of me,  whisper infinity.  i look up in the sky with a haze in my mind.  i feel i'm going to die,  but yet i feel just fine.  i make a smile within me and search and see that there is something inside of me,  whisper infinity.  i take a step away and take one deep breath.  i feel we're going to pay by our eternal death.  right then i see that there is something inside of me,  whisper infinity.  there is a flash of light,  my life passes by.  i turn and day turns to night,  it's dark in the sky.  i realize and see that there is something inside of me,  whisper infinity.

text: abandoned  my flesh melts away sticking to his hands like a spider web with a stench.  burning flesh washing it away with each stroke of my bloody stained paintbrush with in his eyes a possessed soul a hand reaching out grabbing my eyes to see my own vision of the world around cold, desolate,  ive been abandoned. . .  abandoned me alone in the icy cave of  possession demonic sex ive been taken by him again  i've been abandoned by you again with your possessed eyes i was forgotten again with every look from you my flesh burned and melted away and became your thirst.

title: Torn Shadows
author: katelyn
text: torn shadows  embrace my shadows in the dark let you hold them cherish them along with the bloody tears the bloody tears in the  zip lock bag on my night stand my eyes burn with fire the tear up everytime i caress my own arm  i disappointed you so many time broke all my promises memories begin to fade though and i feel better for the moment. . .  i don't miss the cut. . for now i don't miss the blood. . . for now i miss you with your arms around my body sweet kisses upon my neck. . my face. .  you make the scars fade. .  so the tears dont appear anymore i scream for you in love your eyes glow bright white. .  i'm blind by love. .  but am i even blind? or is he perfect. . .  i am blind. . but hes perfect for me i sit in the dark on my own watching at my shadows deteriorate. . . fall into pieces i want you you fix it. . though my shadows arent perfect they have many holes. . but its all the times youve fixed me. . and the peices got blown  away by the breeze. . so you tore yours and put it in mine. . .  and thats what makes us perfect. .  thats what makes me happy. .  that you tore your life to make mine better.

title: I need you to leave

title: I know what I want
author: katelyn
text: you never knew that i wanted so much more from you.  to hold your hand while you meet my parents.  or see a movie with your grandfather.  i always wanted to tell you that i loved you. . . but was afraid that you would leave me.  but that night when you said it,  i froze.  you said what was wrong and i said,  i love you too.  i would'ent let anyone touch me.  not even my parents,  not a hug or a kiss but when you did,  it felt right.  i want you to love me,  i need you.  but when you told me that you cheated.  i slapped your perfect face and you were no longer one with me.

title: German

text: german is,  â“repeat after me,  ich bin vierzehn jara alt. â” â“ish been verzern gara alt. â” opps!  close enough!  german is watching film strips with frau saying,  â“this is this,  and that is that. â”  german is singing songs while waving your hands and doing actions,  having no idea what you are saying.   german is frau lecturing,  â“blah blah blahâ” while whispering to your friends.   german is â“borrowingâ” your friendâ’s worksheet,  â“to see if i did it right. â”  german is making skits; first you go to your house,  get your clothes,  go to the party,   and then bed.   german is watching â“the lion kingâ”; little cartoons talking funny,  and running around.   german is ripping up paper into small pieces,  throwing your confetti,  and getting away with it while your friends go out in the hall.   so,  in other words,   german is doing everything,  but learning german.

title: Red, White, and Blue

title: Our Love for You

title: To
author: kathleen
text: we sit inside our classrooms,  the classrooms filled with self proclaimed work,  where outside the spring flowers bloom,  and where the classmates trick and smirk.   we stare at a white wall,  splotched with pen marks and small drawings,  these are the things we donâ’t install,  the things that are stuck inside and trying to thaw.   deep inside our heads,  the artwork,  experiments,  and writing,  are hiding in a box tied up with a million threads,  with a worry about the fighting.   a fight for the things they love,  the things that come without thought,  the things they dream thereof,  because they'll be thought of as a knot.   to the boy who draws flowers,  who is treated like a naso,   i say put in all your hours,  for you may be the next picasso.   to the lover with the broken heart,   whose head is full of shame,  you are a piece of fine art,  and you deserve to be in a picture frame.   to the dreamer with a spark,  whose head falls asleep everyday,  keep your thoughts away from the dark,  for donâ’t ever let them be led astray.   to the student who is lost,  in the world,  the stars and the sky,  keep your head high at any cost,  for darling your heart will change the worldâ’s eyes.   to the daughter of a forgotten man,  who is treated like a stranger,  lost in the heart of iran,  you will be okay,  you are not in danger.    to the ones who watch night,  as lonely as a neglected train,  who sits day by day on the tracks that are running out of sight,  like a wood beamâ’s story telling grain.   to the ones who feel left behind,  who feel the world is ever as gray,  let me tell you a secret,  that will change your mind,  in the end itâ’ll all be okay.

title: Heaven and His Heroes
author: katrina
text: books with no titles their pages,  empty  i was in a world which wouldn't have ever existed if i hadn't of stubbled on it  a sick joke,  a hoax,  calanders which don't have  months or days.   a pointless,  never-ending lie which rattled the world  if we died once to save this planet we can do it again isn't this philposophy cruel?  reality turns to rubble,  we'll mold it back together won't we? don't give back our old,  yet stable future.   these people,  these grey people,  they walk in straight lines or circles and they do the same thing everyday.  they smirk and usually ignore the earth's battle scars they are blissfully un-aware that i am licking her wounds. . .   one drop,  after another the blood rushes down to the tip of the sword,  at least 3 drops splashes onto his tounge and then he swiftly jabs his sword right into his face hoping he wouldn't rise again,  to be restored once more.

title: Oh, My best friend.
author: katrina
text: at one point i actually thought there was peace on earth and the snow that fell from the sky was virgin i was so naive back then! but deep inside,  i was scared and lost. . .   but with you,  i found myself. . .  tattered and bruised,  not on 2,  but 4 legs like a new born doe. . .   i'm strong and bold like a lion raised by lambs all because you helped me but now it seems the weight of the universe is perched on your shoulder. . .   shame on our people! we're such filthy creatures! plauging the air with our curses/ not giving a damn if a soul is rotting. . .   but even if the world is wrapped in sadness drowning in fear and sorrow,  i'll always try to keep a smile a smile just for you  look at my blood seep through my nails to my fingertips-  just like the time you told me not to bite them or they'll get worse.  but i couldn't help it,   and soon enough my hand went numb.   the world seems to have gone crazy,  hasn't it? maybe 'coz it's spinning too fast?  i bet the moon is yelling,  ''don't bump into the sun!''  i bet the moon is yelling,  ''don't bump into the sun!''

title: Daddy
author: katy
text: i love you daddy.  i miss you so much.   i miss what you smell like,  i miss your touch.  i miss how you talk,  the swagger in your walk.  i miss how you'd tuck us into our beds.  i miss the parades,  the football games,  the late night bruster's trips.  baseball at the park,  swimming at the country club.  the tarzan swing,  the diving boards.   the pavilion,   the parties,  the noodles,  the floaties.  the hugs and the pizza,  the ice cream and kisses.  the flipping,  the floating,  the slides,  and the running.  morning walks,  and butterfly kisses.  the different houses,  the odd numbered holidays.  every other weekend,  half of each summer.  band practice,   school.  play rehearsal,   piano recital.  teach me the peanuts song one more time daddy.  i forgot,  hehe,  i forgot! tiny little text messages,  really short phone calls.  long late night talks while daddy's in florida.  family vacations,  school orientations.  school pictures,  new c. d's,  harry potter books,  video games.   aunt kitty trips,  to when we got sick.   you are my daddy.   you were there through it all.  and now i miss you daddy.  and i've got to stand tall.

title: Teenagers

text: we have to make every day count,   because at the end of the day weâ’ll regret all the chances we didn't take.   we have to be teenagers now,   because we will never get to be teenagers again.   we have to spend our summer night laughing about our stupid mistakes,   because when we become adults our mistakes have consequences.    we have to speak our minds about the things we feel strongly about,   because if we donâ’t then who will?  we have to be kind to each other,  because in the end we only have each other.    and finally we have to make the best of these four years,   because after these four years weâ’ll probably never see each other again.

title: Her scars tell stories,just listen
author: kelly
text: beneath her plaster is a scar.  a cut she does not want anyone to see.  that cut is deep, so is her emotions.  when she takes the plaster off,  you wouldn't understand,  but her scars tell stories, just listen.   the bruise in her face is just to tell you,  what a woman goes through because of men like you.  yes it hurts and we don't show.  but that bruise has a story, all you have to do is listen.   under that cast is a broken heart.  something that stays broken forever.  no matter how much she smiles or laughs,  or even play she has a cast for life,  not even superglue can fix.  this is the longest story and biggest deal but you have to listen.

title: Who Were They?
author: kelly
text: who were they? those who fell,  their lives are stories we now must tell words our hearts are compelled to hear,  but words and stories we cannot bear,  who were they? those who ran to rescue and save,  hurrying and struggling,  they gave,  their all,  when those around them were so afraid,  when life and death decisions had to be made,  who were they? fathers and mothers,  brothers and sisters too,  could be someone close to you,  the living lift up pictures of life and hope,  while looking for news and ways to cope,  who were they? we'll never know them all,  still our duty,  honor,  and call,  from this day forward must only be,  to defend this flag,  this home of the free,  this land of liberty,  and now the message and what bows the knee,  is that we must remember,  they were you,  and they were me.   to honor those whe perished on september 11,  2001 in new york's world trade center.

title: Without A Clue
author: kenyetta
text: i never thought i'd cry myself to sleep.  really,  i never thought i'd love a boy,  and then you proved i could.  i don't understand what you have done.  did you knock me unconscious with your love,  and then poke at my heart for fun? really what have you done? i really need to know,  so it won't ever happen again.  i need to withdraw you from my mind,  heart,  and soul.  but what did you do? how did you overtake me? did you wait until i was in a deep sleep and take my heart in captivity? did you drug me with your charm? that always caused me to falsely fall into your arms? did you hypnotize me chanting that you were the best? that when it comes to loving you i would be obssesd.  did you finally find it; the key to my heart? so whenever you please you can arrive,  and depart.  what did you do? i really need to know.  because for some reason the feelings i have for you i can't let go.  i cried myself to sleep last night,  confused on what i should do.  will the rest of my love life be ruined beacause i'm stuck on loving you?          do you notice or are you blind to see? that just knowing you might always be here,  but not with me is the part that's putting me in misery.  what have you done,  no seriously what did you do? cause i feel like you told my heart a secret and left me without a clue.

title: So Good, So Sweet, That's What You Are

title: Scents of my love
author: kia
text: his voice to me is like the sounds of the ocean breeze in his eyes i can see beyond continents and seas his hair reminds me of blossomed trees and everytime i look at him he makes me feel free the words he speak makes me smile for him i would walk thousands of miles even if it took more than a while when he sleeps he looks like an angel lighter than light and more beautiful than sight he brightens up my day because he is the angel who guides my way through storms and thunder he always makes me wonder his hands are so soft and tender he tastes better than any fruit mixed together in a blender and when i feel cold and sick he touches me gently,  making my heart tick his sweat is sweeter than chocolate and better than candy he's thick and thin and comes in very handy when im sad or stressed he makes me feel more and more blessed and when times get rough he puts his self together and becomes real tough hes my big hero of all times because no matter what he'll always be mine.

title: Sleep my love
author: kia
text: close your eyes babie everything will be alright take it slow babie i still need time to write your in my arms now tight and secure i won't lose you this time our bodies are both pure it's time to take a nap come on,  go ahead sleep on my lap don't be scared i'm right here for you i won't bring down a single tear now go to sleep it's time to put you to rest please no longer weep i'll tell you straight up your the best we're both strangling to be together so let's make this relatioship work,  let's make it clever and i'm taking my time cause i got no worries on my mind as long as your mine then i'll be fine so lay down,  don't worry i'm not in a rush,  i'm not in a hurry close your eyes and drift away i'll still be here when you awake i'll tuck you in,  and kiss you goodnight and as the night runs through i'll make sure to hold you tight.

title: Sisters

title: Our love story
author: kia
text: although we've went our own seperate ways  i still gotta say what i gotta say  our love for each other was just so strong  but the distance between us was never too long  we laughed together through many times  and cried many tears after you were not mine  but even though we can never be together  just remember in my heart is where you'll be forever  the smiles we smiled and the hope we gave  was kept in our minds like an open cave  nobody understood our feelings deep down  but it didn't matter because it never made us frown  we held on tight through roller coasters and rides  and when i looked next to me you were by my side  here to hold my through the many lies  and there to tell my to try and try  i never gave up because i didn't want to lose  but when it came to life i had one choice to choose  we moved together like a happy couple  then time came and we lost each others sight  because the light ahead was not so bright  we thought that we were meant to be  but it was destiny that had lied to me  we fought through dangers and fears  holding back every single tear  and when time came to pass us by  we knew then that it was the end of the line

title: I wish we could forget
author: kim
text: we live in a world of many places and things.  and many people still wonder what tomorrow brings.  but,  what about the things that people still wished to believe.  there isn't many i suppose.   there are a lot of things i wish we could forget.  i wish we could forget the war between two countries that tragedy let.  i wish we could forget the death, the cries,  and frightful gasps.  i wish we could forget the pain.  i wish we could remember the world we had before.  the one time world we had none of those things.  we don't know when the world will stop turning.  why can't we have that back again? i know why we still have the cruel,  the selfish,  the jealous.  there are still more to come.  i wish we could forget them.  i wish we could forget the greed that guides the cruel,  the selfish,  and the jealous.  we need to turn this world around.  we need to start before the world stops.

title: Confused
author: kimberly
text: i am someone else,  someone no one knows.  only i know my real self,  who's stronger than people take me for.  no one can bring my inner self down,  no one knows how.   i am me.   i am looking in the mirror.  it's telling myself i am not cruel,  only truthful.  confused about these words,  not knowing the true meaning.  maybe i should be truthful to myself,  love me for me.  how should i do this when i'm blue,  like the sky in day? but maybe. . . just maybe,  i can look in the mirror and be happy with what i see.

title: More then Friends

text: we see each other every day at school.  we walk together,  we talk to each other at school and over the phone too.  we grew a bond together that is so strong no one can break.  you trust me and i trust you.  we became the best friends.  you may think that we are just friends but i grew to have feelings for you.  it's like everyday i see you i get a smile and my heart beats when i see you.  i don't know what this is.  because i never felt like this way for you.  i don't know what happened.  maybe it is because we talk to each other or because we see each other at school.  i don't know.  one thing that is true about you and why i like you.  it is your personalty,  sense of  humor,  you always know how to make me laugh or when something bad happens you are there for me and i care about you too.  maybe one day you'll realize you might feel the same way about me.  but for now i will keep my feelings for you a secret.

title: My New Teddy Bear
author: kristin
text: i used to have a teddy bear who i would cry to and tell my fears.  she would keep my secrets  and wipe away my tears.  she kept me safe,  she kept me warm.  but then i realized i had a  new teddy bear,  in a different form.  you always stood by my side,  you always lit my way in the dark.  you're the one who knows what's in my heart.  i love you,  please never leave.  stay here and be my new teddy bear.

title: No More Drama
author: kristine
text: i was lost one day but i was found i was tired of all my problems that   were going on.   so i decided to take a walk,   my parents thought it was unusual of me   because i never go for walks.  but i'm so tired of all the drama in my   life.   i was walking down my street wondering   how can i make this stop? so i thought to myself saying: should i run away,  should i do something i might regret,  or should i just talk to my parents and    tell them know how i feel? i thought twice,  no,  i shouldn't run away because where  would i go? no,  i shouldn't do anything stupid that i    might regret.  and no,  i shouldn't talk to my parents  because then they'll start arguing.  so instead of doing all those things i decided to talk to a friend about my problems.  my friend bobby,  who understands me so well,    helped me out with my problems   that i have been wondering about now my problem are all gone and i found   a way to deal with them all.  so all my drama has disappeared and there is no wondering about my drama for the rest of my years.

title: Just Friends
author: kristy
text: i thought we were gonna be just friends.   i was fine with that.   but now that i made that promise to myself,  your the only one i can think of.  i cant concentrate any more.  i wish i could change the way i feel.   maybe then i could go on with life just being your friend.   but i cant.   when someone says your name,  my ears open up to everything after that and nothing else.   when you look at me,  i want to look away but then i might miss something in your eyes that tells me how you feel about me.   i dont want to live like this.   friends arent supposed to feel like this about eachother.   i guess what they say is right.   boys and girls really cant be just friends.   i thought that was dumb,  but now i know it is true.   i cant be just friends with you.

title: Will i heal?
author: kwanele
text: will i heal? my life is a burden because of you.  my life is just sorrow because of you.  my heart keeps bleeding and am telling the truth.  my soul is unhealing,  i have lost hope in me.  will i heal? it's been years that i suffered and it still hurts.  where is my joy? yet you took it from me.  i guess i lost it these years of suffering.  painfull past years i won't forget.  will i heal? life ain't easy for me,  yes it ain't.  you're so brave,  you can make bruises in souls.  aggressiveness and anger you had towards me,  made me not to eat,  sleep or do anything.  i tried easing the pain from this 'me' you've made.  will i heal? the pain you caused me,  had me feeling my body dirty.  pushing and forcing yourself towards me,  showed no manhood but cruelty.  tried scrubbing and scrubbing my body.  i scrubbed till i cried and wished to die.  tried scrubbing,  and the pain you've brought doesn't go away.  will i heal? i admit am a victim,  i got victimized by a man.  an old man whom his age is as my old brother's age.  i was still too young,  thanks god i survived.  the smell of his perfume doesn't go off my chest.  i smelled it a lot of times in some other guys.  i was nine years old,  how could you.  i couldn't fight for myself,  you took advantage of that.  i know it happened years ago,  but the pain seems like a second ago.  and you left me a question i've been asking myself my whole life,  and it's the question am still asking myself now. .  will i heal?

title: Trapped In My Own Conscience
author: kyla
text: i am trapped in my own conscience,  unable to break through,  pounding on the walls of my mind,  but my feet are stuck like glue.  screaming but no one ever seems to hear,  i sink down against the wall,  filled with fear.   i knock on the door but no one ever opens it up,  the glass is filled,  but i canâ’t drink from the cup.  the weight of this world builds up on my head,  look around at my thoughts and am filled with dread.   spiraling,  going in a million different directions,  looking,  back at all the painful collections,  of things that once were and now seem gone,  thinking,  was i only a pawn?  bored,  i look down the old,  dark memory lane,  i search back for when i was once sane.  the happy times start to fill my thoughts a little more,  i finally feel better,  no longer sore.   the door proceeds to open and i walk out into light,  i forget about the pain,  focus on the wonderful sight.   leaving behind the memories that haunted me night and day,  now realizing all i had to do in the first place was pray!  i will never again be stuck in the conscience where pain brews,  no longer succumbing to those ugly blues.  forever now in the presence of god,  i am free to be me,  no longer flawed.   shutting the door that led to my mind,  finally realizing i am one of a kind.   elated that jesus wants me as i am,  perpetually staying with the one who is the lion and the lamb.

title: An Ode to the Odious
author: kyle
text: oh,  helen, your beauty cost a million men their lives see the bloody dead and hear their cries the sun fades out at dawn,  yet it lives anew each day but for the mothers back at home the memories are all that stay oh,  but helen you don't care the war for you is fair for you are the morning and the evening star  mary antoinette,  the king's own darling one silk dresses are the newest thing,  summer palace just for fun women begging in the streets,  groveling for scraps of bread wrenching cries amist the din,  ''my son,  my son is dead!'' oh mary,  you don't care,  for you it's just a game,   live or die,  it's all the same  odious rulers with iron grip,  deep calls out to deep,  luxery's lap is not exempt,  what you sow you're sure to reap,  you forgot the hungry eyes the battlefield of blood too busy with your own affairs to dare to face the mud sin is not forgotten,  the dead demand a price.  my question is to you this day,  ''why couldn't you just be nice?''

text: we're going to eat chad it will be marvelous he never was too relevant,  after all but as a meal,  i'm sure he'll suffice i'll take a leg and i'll gnaw on his bones we'll use his hair as dental floss an eyeball for dessert and for some entertainment we can flick around a tooth or two let's toast to ourselves over cups of his blood let's make merry once again after a drink or two,  chad's lively bones will dance away the hours dance chad dance the bell will toll and we'll all nod off into slumberland wouldn't that be lovely? we're going to eat chad and it will be marvelous.

title: School's Out!
author: laura
text: school's out,  so is the fun.  but look on the bright side summer's almost begun.  we'll stay up late,  sleep in until ten.  hurry up summer,  hurry up and begin.  so goodbye old friends and great teachers,  too.  see you next year cause it's the end of school.

title: Addiction
author: laura
text: why art thou so addicting in my mind? when i weep my eyes find a way to you; walk as i stare through a venetian blind: losing my head and then out of the blue,   your skin soft as a peach collides with mine;  you are in my fantasies,  hopes,  and dreams: we are together always in cloud nine,  regressing and thinking of our teen schemes;  nowadays you have been mine for some time,  but my feelings have still remained the same; just like the wind that blows through an old chime,  and the sight of you in my picture frame:      for now this shall be a victimless crime,      of an addict with little breathing time.

title: In the hood

text: i look out the window the streets covered in snow first time out there i couldn't care  kids all playing ball they said i was too small they wouldn't give me a chance i had to sit there and glance  tears rolling down my face heart beat at a fast pace i couldn't see they were all after me  looking out onto the street friends about to meet watching the thugs on the corner smoking drugs  pop's said id grow up to be good never to be a thug in the hood all them flashing lights it was all apart of the night  watching someone get shot down all because of these dumb clowns living in the hood it's doing me no good

text: best friends are the ones that care about you best friends are the ones that support you in everything you do best friends are the ones that inspire you to follow your dreams best friends are the ones that know your whole life story best friends are the ones that you tell your deepest darkest secrets best friends are the ones that you seek in a time of need best friends are the ones that you recall the funny moments best friends are the ones that cherish all the memories best friends are the sisters that god forgot to give you   best friends. . . everyone has them everyone deserves them. . . .    thanks to erica,  leslie,  liz,  hannah,  janessa,  and kelsey j.  i love ya!

title: Abandoned
author: layla
text: i hate myself.  i left him. . .  but never planned to leave him forever.  i see him,  as this lost little heart,  this abandoned little heart.    and i see a heart,  that beats for me always,  and it can't beat for anyone else.  that kills me.    he can't do anything.  he can't move on.  he's stuck.  longing forever,  for something he'll never have again,  and the only thing he wants.    he wants me to be happy,  even if it's not with him.  and i gotta live with the fact. . .  the fact that i did that.    look at that poor,  lost little puppy.  that sweet,  caring person,  that devoted and loyal person,  that heart that was so true. . .  and so fucking devoted to me.    and always will be.    and i know,  i see how it aches,   and how he hurts,  and longs.    and i know that it's `cause of me. . .  i did that.    it's like looking at a piece of art,  beautiful art,  that i mutilated.  i treated it so good,   for so long.  and then just. . .    every fucking thing can remind us,  of so much.  i have to look at him,  and see him all alone. . .  standing there. . .  looking at me in this nice little setting through a window. . .  seeing me with someone.    happy.  having fun.  in love.    and he's out in the cold. . .    leaving a lover for another,  and watching the other be alone,  missing me.    and having our hearts still long for each other.    and knowing they're all alone.    crying.  and dying inside.  every day.    and all the cold snow that surrounds him all alone,  out there in the dark as he looks in at me with my lover.  trying to smile at me to show he's happy for me. . .  all that snow,  i put it there.  the door that's locked to him.  i locked.  leaving him out there like that. . .    and knowing he's all alone.

title: Good morning
author: leeroy
text: birds out there singing a song   called good morning. . . . .    wake up and look around  the dark night has gone  its just another day  a beautiful day  but filled with lots of surprises  look around the sky  the stars are gone  the moon is gone too   sun comes and shines bright  showing true colours of the day  with  many different ways  its a brand new day  enjoy the fruits of yesterday  fresh air swirling around you  time to plan for tomorrow

title: The Goal of Life
author: leon
text: life is riddle,  unsolved and unwritten.  where is the beginning,  the end,  the middle? it can harsh like a sharp wind or it can be warm like a mitten.    do tell of your story please.  to be told such tales is a pleasure indeed.  you were stuck in mud up to your knees? stung,  you say,  by a swarm of bees?  goal of it,  you ask,  i answer; become what you are and what you want to be.  a painter an artist an electrician and dancer.  pleasure is the key,  my friend.  without it life for people  would come to a rather quick end.  but maybe that definition just suits me.   norms form round,   to the left and to the right.  be different from these boundaries,  thatâ’s normal too.  have accomplishments  you could pile up in a mound,  write rightly and never give up a fight.  be liked and be a leader,  conquer mountains and seas and oceans if you please.  truth be told i had some fun.  who knew! but thatâ’s just between me and you  life is a game,  if youâ’re willing to play,  it makes you think,  it makes you pay.  for a while you stay and then go away,  to prove that you were and said what you wanted to say.   and after all that fun the thing that is important and true; you did what was needed to be done.  did indeed what suited you.

title: Life Was Never Easy
author: lesego
text: as the sun rose every morning; she had to wake up on her knees crawling; seeking for happiness; but it was not easy; because there was never kindness;  as the day went on; she was seeking for survival; but it was never easy; it was never easy because there was never revival;  as the day was passing on; she was seeking for peace; but it was never easy;  day by day; hunting for a better life; she thought of it every night; but it never came to true life;  she thought everything was in a rush; as she never had time to make her life right; life was never easy

title: Really There
author: leslie
text: i see you,  but do you see me? am i another face in the crowd? i watch your mouth and bless your words,  even when they're far too loud.   i glance at your feet and bless your steps.  i hope you will walk this way.  i want to see you,  touch you,  talk to you,  but alas!  you move away!  i need to know if you notice me,  we meet most every day.  but how am i to know for sure? what am i supposed to say?  ''hello,  i love you'' is far too hard,  but then,  so is ''hello'' i open my mouth,  but my words dry up.  i wave and past you go.   why can't i voice the words and feelings that are issuing from my heart? why do i feel empty and alone whenever we're apart?  why can't i let you know right now,   exactly how i feel? why can't i have nerves of iron and a heart shielded with steel?  do you even notice me? do you even know i'm there? or am i just a face and body? am i really there?  i want to tell you all my thoughts,  to speak of my love with a vengeance! however,  my mouth won't move,  i must continue to love at a distance.

title: Change in my life
author: lissette destiny
text: from north to south.  apartment to apartment.  from trains and buses to cars and vans.  now to walk,  its just to far.  lesser clamp buildings.  more open land and space.  i went to a school five floors straight up.  all one building.  i now enter a school half a football field.  all one floor spread out and spaced.  now apartments and houses are in naborhoods.  not owned by landlords.  homes with front yards and neat backyards and attics.  but all the stoops and basements are gone.  all family are miles away.  not down the block or stops away.  the winter is warm.  sparkling white snow is nonexistent.  overcrowding forests in surroundings.  swamps,  lakes,  and rivers are common.  not many lights on at night.  uncomfortably quiet at times.  this is my new home.  and i grew to like it.  from brooklyn,  new york.  to sanford,  florida.  in this world of calamity.

title: That's Just Life
author: liz
text: sitting alone in our rooms full of mourn,  torn,  and sworn we were fore-warned,  we couldn't make much sense,  our bodies completely tense,  minds so dense and hence. . . .  the death of the loved.  we pushed,  we shoved.  anything to get through this horrendous crud,  we were bewildered,  filtered,  sheltered and hidden. . . no one cared if all life was forbidden,  we dug we shoveled,  we swam and sank. . .  but no one cared if its all just a stupid prank,  but in the end the jokes and laughs,  soon fell to deafening sorrowful claps.  many tears were shed,  blood was bled,  hearts were broken,  and the words weren't there to be spoken that day,  just to be seduced by the silence,  and the constant changing of our alliance. . .  we stood up and fought,  sat down and thought,  we laughed we played,  we cried today. . . because of what? because no one can keep their souls shut,  the opening sores of our wounded cut,  there to leak and show us pain,  slow us down in our boundless brain,  prove to us that no ones perfectly sane. . . but who dare to try and disagree,  shall only beg with their innocent plea,  wondering when our minds and spirits will finally be. . . set free.

title: Life as Me
author: liz
text: man,  im so tired.  something inside me needs to be rewired,  or i should be retired.   no one told me that this required. . . strength,  putting my thoughts so far away in length! itâ’s making me feel horrible! everything is looking deplorable.  things in my life are so exhausting,  criss crossing,  a mind boggle. . .  set off with an effective toggle,  leaving me behind restless.   i mean look at this mess! all tattered and torn,  everyone has been sent into a morn,  scorned,  and swore they were warned!!! feeling so helpless over here,  and now its turned into a fear.  my mind is no longer the worry,  things in life seem to be getting so blurry,  if i hurried. . . do you think i'd catch up in time before i was buried?  now its time for me to sleep,  to pass the time in this wondrous deep heap. . . .  but would i dare to leap? if in my dream i came upon a jagged steep? my bodies will power sadly to seep,  laying down to weep. . . if my thoughts were the problem in the first place,  what would happen if our world was in a race? a fast heavy pace,  no grace or embrace. . . no time to climb.  things would be like a mime. . . still silent and distant,  so funny to see but persistent. . . i'll never cease,  trying to find in this world some peace,  for the things that have left a huge crease.

title: Appearing
author: liz
text: behind every beautiful star,  there is something you could never forget.  i found you by luck but luck only keeps you unfortunately so far. . . . . if a smile could go beyond miles and minutes,  i'd smile all day just for you. . . if a wandering ship from the clouds could take me closer,  i'd personally hire the special crew.  people say im just dreaming. . . but i know im completely scheming. . . to find ways to break reality,  because knowing reality it keeps me distant. . from the person who truly makes me happy,  it seems so persistant with its mission,  but i guess thats just ambition.  it's like donald duck in drag,  scooby doo in ''ruv'',  and the littlest smurf up in the front holding our flag.  things only perfectly appear when we want them too,  and im so glad one of them things is you.

title: JENNY'S BAD DAY
author: liza
text: there was a girl named jenny.  she liked to collect pennies,  everybody thought that she was funny.   one day jenny fell in a pool,  when she fell,  she felt like a fool.  then after she got up she started walking to school.   jenny liked to hang out in the sun.   while she was in the sun,  she would eat a muffin bun.  she also like to chew gum.   one day she got gum stuck in her hair.  she needed scissors,  but she couldn't find a pair.   so the gum stayed in her hair.   she also tried peanut butter.  she got so happy,  she got stuck in the gutter.  she got out of the gutter an hour later.
